00:15:45,896 --> 00:15:50,863
<i>He struggled and struggled,
and this is how he’s gonna die</i>

240
00:15:51,277 --> 00:15:56,835
<i>Now, I’ll go take this “inheritance”</i>

241
00:15:57,295 --> 00:16:03,364
<i>I’ll use any means, yes,
to set me on my path</i>

242
00:16:06,394 --> 00:16:11,750
<i>I may have nothing in my hands yet,</i>

243
00:16:12,521 --> 00:16:17,724
<i>That means I’ll start from here</i>

244
00:16:18,965 --> 00:16:24,062
<i>Tell me, Joestar, in the sky over you,</i>

245
00:16:24,663 --> 00:16:31,837
<i>Is the sun shining?</i>

246
00:16:33,257 --> 00:16:37,518
<i>It is, isn’t it, Joestar?</i>

247
00:16:56,408 --> 00:16:57,729
Oh yeah!

248
00:16:57,729 --> 00:17:00,701
You’ve got something good today too, eh?

249
00:17:00,702 --> 00:17:01,900
Give it back!

250
00:17:02,694 --> 00:17:03,694
Over here!

251
00:17:04,312 --> 00:17:10,296
Hey Erina, I heard that
your old man’s a quack!

252
00:17:10,296 --> 00:17:12,072
My father’s a real doctor!

253
00:17:12,072 --> 00:17:16,574
Oh really? This hat looks expensive!

254
00:17:16,574 --> 00:17:19,407
Stop it! It was a birthday
present from my mother!

255
00:17:19,408 --> 00:17:21,138
Stop right there!

256
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,811
What are you doing?! Take this!

257
00:17:30,255 --> 00:17:34,694
I hate when guys try to
act cool in front of girls!

258
00:17:34,905 --> 00:17:37,078
Ow! That hurt!

259
00:17:35,707 --> 00:17:38,697
-Hey, do you know who this guy is?

260
00:17:38,737 --> 00:17:41,094
If he’s that Jonathan kid
from the Joestar family,

261
00:17:41,094 --> 00:17:43,942
I’m gonna give him even
more of a walloping!

262
00:17:45,127 --> 00:17:46,127
Ah-ha!

263
00:17:46,783 --> 00:17:51,450
He <i>is</i> the Joestars’ Jonathan!

264
00:17:54,848 --> 00:17:58,999
Snotty little rich boy! You think
you’re so high and mighty?

265
00:18:02,127 --> 00:18:03,127
Danny!

266
00:18:03,722 --> 00:18:04,722
Eh?!

267
00:18:05,339 --> 00:18:07,832
Let’s go already! Shit!

268
00:18:11,439 --> 00:18:12,987
Uh... Are you alright?

269
00:18:12,988 --> 00:18:14,059
Leave me alone!

270
00:18:14,099 --> 00:18:14,543
But...

271
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:16,527
I did this because I wanted to.

272
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:18,552
I didn’t do it to get you to thank me.

273
00:18:20,012 --> 00:18:22,781
My goal is to become a true gentleman.

274
00:18:23,248 --> 00:18:27,423
You were a damsel in distress,
so I had to stand up for you.

275
00:18:30,807 --> 00:18:32,637
I’ll beat them, someday.

276
00:18:35,110 --> 00:18:36,364
Let’s go, Danny!

277
00:18:36,388 --> 00:18:37,488
Oh, wait!

278
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:46,787
Jonathan Joestar...

279
00:19:21,054 --> 00:19:22,054
You...

280
00:19:22,681 --> 00:19:24,237
You must be Dio Brando!

281
00:19:25,236 --> 00:19:27,412
And you’re...

282
00:19:27,768 --> 00:19:28,935
Jonathan Joestar?

283
00:19:28,936 --> 00:19:31,249
Everyone calls me JoJo. Nice to meet you!

284
00:19:31,735 --> 00:19:33,535
Ah, Danny! I’ll introduce you.

285
00:19:33,559 --> 00:19:36,044
This is my friend, Danny.
He’s a clever old hound!

286
00:19:36,203 --> 00:19:38,473
Oh, and don’t worry about him biting!

287
00:19:38,497 --> 00:19:39,497
Friend?

288
00:19:39,536 --> 00:19:40,525
Yeah!

289
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:45,444
Danny! What was that for!

290
00:19:45,444 --> 00:19:46,444
Danny!

291
00:19:47,348 --> 00:19:48,508
You won’t get away with this!

292
00:19:48,509 --> 00:19:51,182
We’ve been waiting for you, Dio Brando.

293
00:19:53,235 --> 00:19:54,235
Lord Joestar!

294
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,174
Come inside!

295
00:19:56,901 --> 00:20:01,078
From today on, you’ll be
living here in our mansion.

296
00:20:02,537 --> 00:20:03,883
Something wrong, JoJo?

297
00:20:04,117 --> 00:20:05,317
Ah, nothing.

298
00:20:06,022 --> 00:20:09,087
You’ve travelled all the way from
London, Dio. You must be tired.

299
00:20:09,323 --> 00:20:12,621
Starting today, you are part of our family.

300
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:16,708
You’ll be given the same
kind of life as my son, JoJo.

301
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:17,375
Yes!

302
00:20:17,376 --> 00:20:20,169
I am grateful for your
kindness, Lord Joestar.

303
00:20:21,546 --> 00:20:22,546
Mister Brando!

304
00:20:22,921 --> 00:20:24,570
I’m Police Inspector Archer!

305
00:20:25,317 --> 00:20:27,190
Police? Has something happened?

306
00:20:27,190 --> 00:20:28,051
Oh, no!

307
00:20:28,396 --> 00:20:31,143
I’m an old friend of the Joestars.

308
00:20:31,999 --> 00:20:35,195
Although, I could hear Danny
whimper a moment ago...

309
00:20:35,276 --> 00:20:36,181
Ah, that was—

310
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:38,041
-He came at me so suddenly.

311
00:20:38,421 --> 00:20:41,815
When I jumped in surprise,
I think my leg may have hit him!

312
00:20:41,816 --> 00:20:45,657
Danny is the Joestar household’s
wonderful guard dog.

313
00:20:46,184 --> 00:20:51,530
He’s a friendly creature, but
I’m sorry he surprised you.

314
00:20:52,239 --> 00:20:53,239
JoJo!

315
00:20:53,758 --> 00:20:56,435
You’ll let this Danny matter go, right?

316
00:20:57,918 --> 00:20:58,599
Yes, sir.

317
00:20:58,599 --> 00:20:59,437
Good.

318
00:21:00,131 --> 00:21:05,322
JoJo has lost his mother too—
and you both are the same age!

319
00:21:05,322 --> 00:21:07,457
Make sure to get along with each other.

320
00:21:08,373 --> 00:21:10,854
Now, allow me to show you to your room.

321
00:21:11,179 --> 00:21:12,179
Mister Brando!

322
00:21:15,611 --> 00:21:16,655
Nice to have met you!

323
00:21:20,126 --> 00:21:21,126
Ta-ta, JoJo!

324
00:21:29,324 --> 00:21:30,656
Now then, let me get—

325
00:21:30,719 --> 00:21:32,028
Watch it!

326
00:21:32,504 --> 00:21:34,372
Don’t touch my bag!

327
00:21:34,373 --> 00:21:35,496
I was just trying to carry it for—

328
00:21:35,521 --> 00:21:36,528
That’s enough.

329
00:21:37,965 --> 00:21:40,521
Your hand is covered in dog drool.

330
00:21:40,935 --> 00:21:43,415
Pardon me if I don’t want
it all over my things!

331
00:21:45,772 --> 00:21:49,071
Alright JoJo, I’ll tell
you from the get-go.

332
00:21:49,414 --> 00:21:51,914
I like being the best!
I’m always number one!

333
00:21:52,524 --> 00:21:55,008
I don’t care who you are,
no one looks down on me!

334
00:21:55,046 --> 00:21:57,229
I was only trying to be friendly!

335
00:21:57,423 --> 00:22:00,098
What are you two doing?

336
00:22:02,647 --> 00:22:04,155
And one more thing—

337
00:22:06,352 --> 00:22:08,440
I hate dogs.

338
00:22:09,302 --> 00:22:12,572
The way they grovel and suck
up to humans disgusts me.

339
00:22:12,644 --> 00:22:15,413
Keep your stupid dog away from me!

340
00:22:16,578 --> 00:22:18,634
Coming, Lord Joestar!

341
00:22:27,073 --> 00:22:32,073
Thus, with this meeting, the
two boys’ youth had begun.

342
00:22:52,060 --> 00:22:55,305
Are you coming, JoJo, Dio?

343
00:22:55,422 --> 00:23:03,161
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

344
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:11,070
<i>We take on the duty of
becoming true gentlemen</i>

345
00:23:11,904 --> 00:23:15,902
<i>This is why we study, acquire knowledge,</i>

346
00:23:12,902 --> 00:23:14,602
{\an8}<i>(Without pause!)</i>

347
00:23:14,886 --> 00:23:16,586
{\an8}<i>(Without limit!)</i>

348
00:23:15,934 --> 00:23:18,950
<i>And arm ourselves with logic!</i>

349
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:19,918
{\an8}<i>(So you’ll never lose!)</i>

350
00:23:19,942 --> 00:23:21,964
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>

351
00:23:21,965 --> 00:23:26,715
<i>For the sake of heading
the house of Joestar</i>

352
00:23:25,917 --> 00:23:28,153
{\an8}<i>(The honourable Joestars!)</i>

353
00:23:27,031 --> 00:23:31,423
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

354
00:23:31,423 --> 00:23:35,393
<i>The same mistakes once again</i>

355
00:23:35,394 --> 00:23:38,630
<i>How many times have
you made them! Six times!</i>

356
00:23:39,531 --> 00:23:43,932
<i>Dio has all of them correct!</i>

357
00:23:44,395 --> 00:23:46,808
It’s just because I love reading so much!

358
00:23:46,808 --> 00:23:49,307
But they haven’t even
taught us this in school yet!

359
00:23:57,313 --> 00:24:05,393
<i>Bear in mind, as proud nobles,</i>

360
00:24:05,393 --> 00:24:12,954
<i>We behave like true gentlemen</i>

361
00:24:13,884 --> 00:24:18,041
<i>Sit up straight, use your knife with grace,</i>

362
00:24:14,914 --> 00:24:16,882
{\an8}<i>(So elegantly!)</i>

363
00:24:16,906 --> 00:24:18,636
{\an8}<i>(So gracefully!)</i>

364
00:24:18,073 --> 00:24:21,851
<i>So that your mouth always remains spotless</i>

365
00:24:20,398 --> 00:24:21,798
{\an8}<i>(Unfailingly!)</i>

366
00:24:21,922 --> 00:24:23,920
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>

367
00:24:23,921 --> 00:24:28,563
<i>For the sake of being loved as a Joestar!</i>

368
00:24:27,919 --> 00:24:30,435
{\an8}<i>(The proud Joestars!)</i>

369
00:24:28,935 --> 00:24:32,984
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

370
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:37,420
<i>Do you call yourself a gentleman?</i>

371
00:24:37,420 --> 00:24:41,396
<i>Look at Dio’s elegant touch</i>

372
00:24:41,397 --> 00:24:45,497
<i>His manners are perfect!</i>

373
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:49,991
<i>Take away JoJo’s plates!
You will go without dinner tonight!</i>

374
00:24:49,991 --> 00:24:52,951
<i>Observe and follow Dio’s example</i>

375
00:24:53,419 --> 00:25:02,547
<i>I am embarrassed by
how much I’ve spoiled you</i>

376
00:25:02,580 --> 00:25:03,580
But...

377
00:25:03,905 --> 00:25:08,279
My mother taught me well. She
always made sure I sat up straight.

378
00:25:11,342 --> 00:25:18,380
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

379
00:25:18,611 --> 00:25:27,605
<i>In our hearts we must always consider
questions of philosophy and justice</i>

380
00:25:29,150 --> 00:25:33,229
In our great England, a tale of two knights
has been passed down for generations.

381
00:25:33,230 --> 00:25:38,084
One day, their master was
taken prisoner by the enemy.

382
00:25:38,815 --> 00:25:43,782
The enemy was afraid of the
two knights, who had great power.

383
00:25:43,782 --> 00:25:45,335
And so she gave them this condition:

384
00:25:46,624 --> 00:25:53,764
“If you two will be executed in her place,
I will guarantee the life of your master.”

385
00:25:55,354 --> 00:25:57,431
Here is my question for you:

386
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:58,680
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

387
00:25:59,395 --> 00:26:06,044
Those two knights who gave themselves
up as prisoners to save their master;

388
00:26:06,945 --> 00:26:10,665
What was the first thing they
saw through their prison bars?

389
00:26:11,046 --> 00:26:14,219
Was it the mud that lay before their eyes?

390
00:26:14,769 --> 00:26:20,158
Or was it the stars shining above them?

391
00:26:20,936 --> 00:26:22,689
What do you think?

392
00:26:23,801 --> 00:26:24,901
The stars?

393
00:26:25,944 --> 00:26:27,044
Or the mud?

394
00:26:29,174 --> 00:26:30,174
I...

395
00:26:33,028 --> 00:26:34,880
I think they were looking at the mud.

396
00:26:36,585 --> 00:26:38,240
What’s your reasoning?

397
00:26:39,057 --> 00:26:44,482
In the end, they had no choice
but to die for their master.

398
00:26:45,375 --> 00:26:48,446
You can’t achieve anything if you’re dead.

399
00:26:48,446 --> 00:26:51,071
So no matter what tricks
they would have had to pull,

400
00:26:51,111 --> 00:26:53,184
I think they should have stayed
alive and done something!

401
00:26:53,222 --> 00:26:54,222
I think...

402
00:26:55,553 --> 00:26:57,323
They were looking at the stars!

403
00:26:57,854 --> 00:26:59,665
They held onto their honour!

404
00:26:59,666 --> 00:27:02,187
The names of those two knights
will be etched into history!

405
00:27:02,194 --> 00:27:03,394
So what!

406
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:05,480
So what?

407
00:27:08,538 --> 00:27:12,173
The way one lives, and the things
one does, those are important!

408
00:27:12,174 --> 00:27:13,474
But they—

409
00:27:14,379 --> 00:27:17,715
They were left empty-handed
in the end!

410
00:27:18,005 --> 00:27:19,305
Such regret...

411
00:27:20,331 --> 00:27:21,631
Such powerlessness...

412
00:27:22,630 --> 00:27:24,244
What they saw was the mud!

413
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:28,505
Their lesson is to teach us what
we can achieve by staying alive!

414
00:27:28,506 --> 00:27:30,371
They held onto their
pride until the very end!

415
00:27:30,372 --> 00:27:33,345
They were looking at the stars! I think
they’re teaching us <i>how</i> we should live!

416
00:27:33,345 --> 00:27:34,445
Listen!

417
00:27:35,337 --> 00:27:37,916
You’re a noble! You have it all!

418
00:27:37,916 --> 00:27:39,721
You’ve lived by taking
from those beneath you!

419
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:45,289
So isn’t it your responsibility to think
about what you’ll achieve with your life?

420
00:27:45,356 --> 00:27:45,991
I—

421
00:27:45,992 --> 00:27:48,388
That’s enough, you two.

422
00:27:49,742 --> 00:27:53,251
There’s no right answer to this question.

423
00:27:53,999 --> 00:27:55,132
Bear in mind—

424
00:27:55,846 --> 00:28:00,312
<i>All people live in a prison called fate</i>

425
00:28:00,391 --> 00:28:04,495
<i>Reaching out through those bars,</i>

426
00:28:04,816 --> 00:28:09,274
<i>Do they see the stars? Or the mud?</i>

427
00:28:09,337 --> 00:28:14,706
<i>Either one could be said to be correct</i>

428
00:28:42,023 --> 00:28:44,370
<i>A world without disparity, that’s sports</i>

429
00:28:44,370 --> 00:28:46,704
<i>Where courage alone
has the chance to overturn</i>

430
00:28:46,704 --> 00:28:49,609
<i>Get ready to rumble! Fanaticism
overcomes all differences</i>

431
00:28:49,783 --> 00:28:53,171
<i>This is straight up religion!
If you lose, instant fucking funeral!</i>

432
00:28:53,196 --> 00:28:55,482
<i>All eyes on are on this ritual
where triumph goes to the victor</i>

433
00:28:55,507 --> 00:28:57,243
<i>Everyone, gather around!</i>

434
00:28:57,268 --> 00:28:59,244
<i>The winner is a sweeping hero</i>

435
00:28:59,307 --> 00:29:00,990
<i>Who will be declared king?!</i>

436
00:29:00,990 --> 00:29:02,737
<i>The opening bell rings</i>

437
00:29:02,737 --> 00:29:05,395
<i>Here comes today’s challenger!</i>

438
00:29:07,292 --> 00:29:07,792
Oi!

439
00:29:08,475 --> 00:29:10,348
Hey hey, JoJo JoJo!

440
00:29:23,853 --> 00:29:26,924
Right in the face! The winner is Joestar!

441
00:29:26,924 --> 00:29:28,679
Our new champion!

442
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,029
You did it, JoJo!

443
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:31,671
Danny would be proud!

444
00:29:31,672 --> 00:29:36,137
Now, who will be the next to
challenge our champion, JoJo?

445
00:29:36,138 --> 00:29:37,761
Is there anyone?

446
00:29:37,770 --> 00:29:39,714
Everyone listen up!

447
00:29:39,715 --> 00:29:44,715
A new face has just asked to join our game.

448
00:29:44,829 --> 00:29:47,965
His name is Dio Brando!

449
00:29:48,263 --> 00:29:50,000
Dio Brando?

450
00:29:48,827 --> 00:29:53,780
-Shall we tell our new friend
how we do things here?

451
00:29:53,938 --> 00:29:55,294
Yeah! Do it!

452
00:29:55,294 --> 00:29:57,717
Alright, let’s do it!

453
00:29:57,047 --> 00:29:57,747
-Good!

454
00:29:57,769 --> 00:30:00,325
The rule is if you get
hit in the face once, you—

455
00:30:00,325 --> 00:30:02,825
Don’t worry, I played by the
 same rules back in London.

456
00:30:02,826 --> 00:30:05,605
That’s the bell!

457
00:30:04,073 --> 00:30:05,611
-Go, JoJo!

458
00:30:05,612 --> 00:30:07,140
Beat him up!

459
00:30:07,834 --> 00:30:09,265
What is this move!

460
00:30:09,289 --> 00:30:10,704
I’ve never seen it before!

461
00:30:10,728 --> 00:30:11,966
Oi, JoJo!

462
00:30:27,228 --> 00:30:30,053
That’s a hit to the face!

463
00:30:30,053 --> 00:30:31,053
He lost!

464
00:30:32,815 --> 00:30:35,585
Our king! Our king!

465
00:30:35,585 --> 00:30:38,085
Dio! Dio! Dio! Dio!

466
00:30:38,110 --> 00:30:39,839
My eye!

467
00:30:39,839 --> 00:30:41,586
Guys, guys, guys!

468
00:30:43,601 --> 00:30:47,847
I think my finger went in his eye.

469
00:30:48,622 --> 00:30:52,243
I must forfeit my win. I have
to leave now, excuse me!

470
00:30:51,951 --> 00:30:52,457
-Hey, hey!

471
00:30:52,457 --> 00:30:56,702
Dio, you were amazing!
How do you move like that?

472
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:58,869
Teach me!

473
00:30:59,521 --> 00:31:01,205
Guys! Ow...

474
00:31:07,473 --> 00:31:08,613
Danny...

475
00:31:11,342 --> 00:31:16,287
Why is Dio always trying to bring me down?

476
00:31:18,602 --> 00:31:20,958
It feels like he’s invading my life.

477
00:31:26,331 --> 00:31:30,101
<i>Hey, Danny, my heart aches</i>

478
00:31:32,592 --> 00:31:35,811
<i>And I’m filled with worry</i>

479
00:31:38,907 --> 00:31:44,682
<i>What if I were to die today?</i>

480
00:31:45,241 --> 00:31:50,454
<i>Would anyone cry for me?</i>

481
00:31:51,587 --> 00:31:56,320
<i>You’re always so understanding</i>

482
00:31:58,395 --> 00:32:02,867
<i>Thank you for staying by my side!</i>

483
00:32:04,187 --> 00:32:10,175
<i>If mum were still here,
would it feel this way?</i>

484
00:32:10,489 --> 00:32:16,545
<i>Would she love me this way?</i>

485
00:32:24,012 --> 00:32:25,012
You’re...

486
00:32:36,812 --> 00:32:38,358
My hanky...

487
00:32:40,736 --> 00:32:43,220
Oi! Thanks for bringing
my handkerchief back!

488
00:32:43,220 --> 00:32:45,832
Hey, I’ll be back here tomorrow too,

489
00:32:45,856 --> 00:32:47,755
So stop by again!

490
00:32:47,779 --> 00:32:48,636
Danny!

491
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,609
Has it caught your fancy?

492
00:33:06,555 --> 00:33:08,871
Please excuse me for
grabbing it without permission.

493
00:33:09,039 --> 00:33:10,252
It’s alright.

494
00:33:11,144 --> 00:33:16,363
They say this Stone Mask was
unearthed in some Mexican ruins.

495
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:17,800
Mexico...

496
00:33:17,809 --> 00:33:18,776
Mm-hmm.

497
00:33:19,571 --> 00:33:25,316
We bought it from a London art dealer,
around the time JoJo was born.

498
00:33:26,396 --> 00:33:29,620
On the way back,
we had a carriage accident.

499
00:33:30,531 --> 00:33:33,558
That was the time your dear
father saved us, you know.

500
00:33:36,101 --> 00:33:38,229
Are you interested in it?

501
00:33:39,023 --> 00:33:41,361
Oh, no. Not especially.

502
00:33:43,641 --> 00:33:44,635
Uh...

503
00:33:46,116 --> 00:33:49,225
JoJo is always out playing
with Danny, isn’t he?

504
00:33:49,870 --> 00:33:55,519
It’s because of the trust and
friendship Danny has in JoJo.

505
00:33:55,940 --> 00:33:58,082
Friendship? With a dog?

506
00:33:59,194 --> 00:34:03,928
I had bought Danny when JoJo was young.

507
00:34:04,874 --> 00:34:09,794
At first, he was afraid
of unfamiliar people,

508
00:34:09,935 --> 00:34:12,597
And he didn’t get on well with JoJo yet.

509
00:34:14,301 --> 00:34:19,003
But one time, JoJo was drowning in a river.

510
00:34:21,441 --> 00:34:25,376
There wasn’t even one person
around who could hear his voice.

511
00:34:26,743 --> 00:34:28,949
Just when JoJo was about to drown...

512
00:34:28,949 --> 00:34:33,083
A figure, hearing his screams,
flew down to the river.

513
00:34:33,083 --> 00:34:34,095
It was Danny!

514
00:34:35,202 --> 00:34:39,390
He dove in and saved JoJo’s life.

515
00:34:41,367 --> 00:34:46,970
Danny was brave to have risked
his own life to save another.

516
00:34:48,263 --> 00:34:55,973
Young JoJo was moved by Danny’s bravery.

517
00:34:57,632 --> 00:35:01,535
That’s when JoJo truly
became friends with him.

518
00:35:02,363 --> 00:35:03,307
Is that so?

519
00:35:03,331 --> 00:35:04,077
M’lord.

520
00:35:04,077 --> 00:35:06,550
Eh? Ah, that’s right.

521
00:35:12,467 --> 00:35:14,467
Friends...

522
00:35:17,718 --> 00:35:18,877
Erina!

523
00:35:18,877 --> 00:35:19,671
JoJo!

524
00:35:19,687 --> 00:35:21,687
The two met once more!

525
00:35:22,344 --> 00:35:26,835
Love! That wonderful curiosity
that guided JoJo’s actions.

526
00:35:26,835 --> 00:35:30,641
JoJo was instantly
head over heels for her.

527
00:35:32,395 --> 00:35:33,395
Danny!

528
00:35:33,981 --> 00:35:35,021
Come boy!

529
00:35:38,825 --> 00:35:43,385
Oh, you’re so clever to eat
the fruit but not the core.

530
00:35:45,144 --> 00:35:47,612
Hey JoJo, what are you carving over there?

531
00:35:47,613 --> 00:35:50,713
Huh? It’s nothing.

532
00:35:50,714 --> 00:35:51,921
What are you hiding?

533
00:35:51,944 --> 00:35:53,507
It’s nothing interesting.

534
00:35:53,507 --> 00:35:55,340
When you say it like that, it makes
me want to see it even more!

535
00:35:55,340 --> 00:35:56,523
You’ll just laugh!

536
00:35:56,523 --> 00:35:57,960
I won’t laugh.

537
00:35:58,027 --> 00:35:58,924
You’ll tell people!

538
00:35:58,924 --> 00:36:00,138
I won’t tell, so show me!

539
00:36:00,139 --> 00:36:01,258
I told you, no!

540
00:36:01,259 --> 00:36:02,444
JoJo!

541
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,000
Oh, my!

542
00:36:06,318 --> 00:36:13,849
<i>Erina, just saying your
name makes me feel at ease</i>

543
00:36:14,312 --> 00:36:22,200
<i>Any musician would fall
in love with its melody</i>

544
00:36:22,707 --> 00:36:26,038
<i>It puts me in such a good mood</i>

545
00:36:26,062 --> 00:36:26,843
Oh!

546
00:36:26,867 --> 00:36:29,933
<i>To be laughing like this</i>

547
00:36:30,808 --> 00:36:38,008
<i>There’s nothing but blue skies
here in vibrant Liverpool</i>

548
00:36:38,294 --> 00:36:39,967
<i>Erina</i>

549
00:36:40,262 --> 00:36:41,879
<i>JoJo</i>

550
00:36:42,587 --> 00:36:45,916
<i>Our happiness is right here</i>

551
00:36:45,916 --> 00:36:53,424
<i>The clouds are proud, and
the wind’s a little sweet</i>

552
00:36:54,299 --> 00:36:55,993
<i>JoJo</i>

553
00:36:56,267 --> 00:36:58,128
<i>Erina</i>

554
00:36:58,798 --> 00:37:01,966
<i>There aren’t enough words</i>

555
00:37:01,966 --> 00:37:08,860
<i>For these ever overflowing feelings</i>

556
00:37:10,209 --> 00:37:18,315
<i>I want to hear your voice
say, “it makes me happy”</i>

557
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:23,293
<i>That would be so
embarrassing, you—</i>

558
00:37:24,007 --> 00:37:25,746
<i>Scoundrel!</i>

559
00:37:26,756 --> 00:37:33,663
<i>I don’t know why, but I’m drawn to you</i>

560
00:37:34,709 --> 00:37:42,209
<i>Then find a reason,
let’s make it our reason!</i>

561
00:37:42,294 --> 00:37:44,241
<i>Your hand,</i>

562
00:37:44,265 --> 00:37:46,277
<i>My hand,</i>

563
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:49,680
<i>When they’re apart I feel so lost</i>

564
00:37:49,833 --> 00:37:57,488
<i>It gives me a little courage
to move forward to tomorrow</i>

565
00:37:58,232 --> 00:38:06,260
<i>Our hearts are resonating,
beating in time</i>

566
00:38:06,292 --> 00:38:16,274
<i>Drawing us together, these
fleeting feelings surround us</i>

567
00:38:20,321 --> 00:38:21,512
It’s already this late!

568
00:38:22,439 --> 00:38:25,082
We have a guest coming
tonight, I have to hurry home.

569
00:38:25,913 --> 00:38:26,913
Erina!

570
00:38:27,088 --> 00:38:28,088
I’ll see you tomorrow!

571
00:38:28,604 --> 00:38:29,866
Yes, JoJo!

572
00:38:29,866 --> 00:38:30,721
Danny!

573
00:38:34,237 --> 00:38:42,197
<i>The one I’m so strongly
drawn to, his name is...</i>

574
00:38:42,197 --> 00:38:50,108
<i>Jonathan Joestar</i>

575
00:38:57,148 --> 00:38:58,148
Hey!

576
00:39:00,268 --> 00:39:01,982
You’re Erina Pendleton, right?

577
00:39:03,291 --> 00:39:08,088
I heard you were hanging
out with JoJo today.

578
00:39:08,844 --> 00:39:09,844
Umm...

579
00:39:10,122 --> 00:39:11,222
What do you...

580
00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:41,328
He...

581
00:39:41,328 --> 00:39:42,876
He did it!

582
00:39:42,900 --> 00:39:44,511
That’s our Dio!

583
00:39:44,511 --> 00:39:47,844
He does the things we’re too chicken
to, and with such confidence too!

584
00:39:47,844 --> 00:39:51,695
I’ve got goosebumps!
I want to be just like him!

585
00:39:55,269 --> 00:39:57,441
Have you kissed JoJo yet?

586
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,278
You haven’t, have you?

587
00:40:03,791 --> 00:40:06,974
The first person you kissed wasn’t JoJo...

588
00:40:06,974 --> 00:40:08,585
It was me, Dio!

589
00:40:09,697 --> 00:40:14,358
You know what this sort of thing
means for a lady’s reputation, right?

590
00:40:17,315 --> 00:40:18,037
Hey!

591
00:40:18,046 --> 00:40:19,664
She’s—!

592
00:40:19,673 --> 00:40:21,508
You bitch!

593
00:40:22,210 --> 00:40:24,920
What are you doing washing
my kiss away with mud?!

594
00:40:34,939 --> 00:40:38,382
<i>Dio...</i>

595
00:40:39,329 --> 00:40:43,445
<i>Dio...</i>

596
00:40:43,767 --> 00:40:45,609
Get up, bitch!

597
00:40:45,609 --> 00:40:48,339
What’re you sleeping for?

598
00:40:48,737 --> 00:40:52,039
Oi, why’s the booze gone?!

599
00:40:52,039 --> 00:40:56,367
Who do you think puts
food on the table? Stupid bitch!

600
00:40:56,377 --> 00:40:58,560
Hey, now go buy some booze!

601
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:01,425
Father, mother’s clearly not well!

602
00:41:01,425 --> 00:41:04,403
She’s just fakin’ it!

603
00:41:04,791 --> 00:41:06,679
Oi, you hear me?

604
00:41:05,521 --> 00:41:07,021
-Stop it, Father!

605
00:41:07,195 --> 00:41:08,671
Mum! Mum!

606
00:41:08,687 --> 00:41:10,893
I’m sorry! Please forgive me!

607
00:41:10,894 --> 00:41:13,530
Of course you shouldn’t go to the shops!

608
00:41:13,633 --> 00:41:18,889
I’ve hurt you. I’m a good-for-nothin’.
Please forgive me!

609
00:41:19,006 --> 00:41:22,131
In tough times like these, I’ve
gotta work for your sake too.

610
00:41:22,131 --> 00:41:24,623
Please, you’ve got to get well!

611
00:41:27,281 --> 00:41:31,225
<i>Dio...</i>

612
00:41:31,678 --> 00:41:35,906
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

613
00:41:33,196 --> 00:41:35,539
-Mum! Mum!

614
00:41:36,006 --> 00:41:39,293
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

615
00:41:40,063 --> 00:41:43,113
Dio boy, go and buy me booze!

616
00:41:43,338 --> 00:41:44,760
But our money’s already—

617
00:41:44,785 --> 00:41:47,017
Are you talking back?!

618
00:41:47,055 --> 00:41:49,021
You got money from that
factory job, don’t ya?

619
00:41:49,021 --> 00:41:52,146
Please, leave some money
for medicine at least!

620
00:41:52,154 --> 00:41:54,201
You’re really gonna
disobey me, you bastard?

621
00:41:54,226 --> 00:41:54,795
Father!

622
00:41:54,796 --> 00:41:58,530
You really expect me to
work my arse off for you? Idiot!

623
00:42:00,312 --> 00:42:03,601
You’re all trying to make a fool of me!

624
00:42:03,714 --> 00:42:06,703
After all the trouble I went
through to nick that noble’s shit!

625
00:42:06,977 --> 00:42:09,598
That’s it. That noble, Joestar.

626
00:42:09,598 --> 00:42:11,808
Why don’t I send him a letter...

627
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:13,290
No...

628
00:42:14,598 --> 00:42:17,130
You and I are different!

629
00:42:19,735 --> 00:42:22,917
<i>Dio...</i>

630
00:42:24,029 --> 00:42:27,824
<i>Dio...</i>

631
00:42:28,426 --> 00:42:30,442
<i>Dio...</i>

632
00:42:30,506 --> 00:42:31,575
Dio!!

633
00:42:32,174 --> 00:42:35,332
<i>Dio...</i>

634
00:42:37,293 --> 00:42:43,301
<i>Dio, how could you do such a thing?
How could you hurt her like that!</i>

635
00:42:43,412 --> 00:42:49,412
<i>What in the world have I ever done
to you?! Can you tell me, Dio?</i>

636
00:42:49,765 --> 00:42:54,033
<i>You’re so amazing, so
much more than I am</i>

637
00:42:54,033 --> 00:42:55,385
I admired you!

638
00:42:56,088 --> 00:43:02,375
<i>But now there is a single
flame that burns in my heart</i>

639
00:43:03,633 --> 00:43:04,633
Dio!

640
00:43:08,936 --> 00:43:11,948
<i>Aren’t you using my name</i>

641
00:43:11,948 --> 00:43:13,990
<i>DIO: A little too lightly?
JOJO: I’ll never forgive you!</i>

642
00:43:13,990 --> 00:43:18,147
<i>So you’ve heard? What I
did to your beloved Erina?</i>

643
00:43:16,393 --> 00:43:18,147
-You’ve disgraced her!

644
00:43:18,201 --> 00:43:21,678
DIO: I bet you’re mad with jealousy!
<i>JOJO: This is for her sake, not mine!</i>

645
00:43:27,601 --> 00:43:33,118
<i>I have to stand up to him, even
if I can’t beat him. I cannot lose!</i>

646
00:43:34,141 --> 00:43:39,863
<i>Control your emotions, you’re
different from that drunken lout</i>

647
00:43:40,331 --> 00:43:45,998
<i>On the blood resonating in my heart,
I swear to restore her honour, Dio! </i>

648
00:43:46,561 --> 00:43:52,542
<i>I’ll put you back in your place,
I’ll teach you a lesson you won’t forget</i>

649
00:43:55,258 --> 00:43:55,838
Come at me!

650
00:43:56,298 --> 00:43:59,270
<i>This new power arising within me</i>

651
00:43:59,488 --> 00:44:00,972
It feels so good!

652
00:44:08,705 --> 00:44:12,425
<i>You’re the one who lit this fire in me</i>

653
00:44:13,277 --> 00:44:14,277
Dio!

654
00:44:15,174 --> 00:44:23,774
<i>I won’t stop beating you until you cry!</i>

655
00:44:27,824 --> 00:44:31,094
<i>How dare you do this to me?</i>

656
00:44:31,094 --> 00:44:33,851
<i>You miserable insect!</i>

657
00:44:34,252 --> 00:44:36,924
<i>You scum of the earth!</i>

658
00:44:37,307 --> 00:44:43,623
<i>How dare such scum like
you come at me, Dio!</i>

659
00:44:43,623 --> 00:44:48,732
<i>Me, the great Dio!</i>

660
00:44:52,314 --> 00:44:54,185
What on earth is going on?!

661
00:44:55,219 --> 00:44:58,804
You two! You’ll be punished for this!
Now go back to your rooms!

662
00:45:11,560 --> 00:45:12,560
Dio...

663
00:45:13,267 --> 00:45:16,328
That stupid kiss of yours hurt
me more than you intended!

664
00:45:21,765 --> 00:45:23,033
Ah... Eri—

665
00:45:26,727 --> 00:45:29,039
I feel so miserable!

666
00:45:31,317 --> 00:45:33,533
I’ve never felt pain like this before...

667
00:45:33,549 --> 00:45:34,549
Erina!

668
00:45:35,603 --> 00:45:40,884
Erina! Did you say goodbye
to all your friends?

669
00:45:43,379 --> 00:45:44,579
Yes, Father.

670
00:45:45,173 --> 00:45:49,197
I’m sorry for imposing my career
on you. Even though I know you—

671
00:45:49,197 --> 00:45:50,197
Let’s go.

672
00:45:51,221 --> 00:45:53,068
I’ll make friends over there too.

673
00:45:58,655 --> 00:45:59,655
Erina...

674
00:46:00,671 --> 00:46:02,806
I underestimated JoJo.

675
00:46:04,449 --> 00:46:06,576
His explosive power...

676
00:46:07,802 --> 00:46:09,480
His resilience...

677
00:46:10,491 --> 00:46:12,549
I have to become stronger...

678
00:46:13,951 --> 00:46:16,086
So that I can become
a gentleman at heart!

679
00:46:16,807 --> 00:46:20,557
I have to control my anger and stay calm...

680
00:46:22,993 --> 00:46:25,062
So that I can take everything from him!

681
00:46:43,973 --> 00:46:45,011
However...

682
00:46:54,372 --> 00:46:55,435
What’s that noise?

683
00:46:58,341 --> 00:47:00,464
Could someone be
inside the incinerator?

684
00:47:01,615 --> 00:47:03,198
Are they trying to get out?!

685
00:47:03,670 --> 00:47:04,670
Ah, it burns!

686
00:47:09,288 --> 00:47:10,288
Danny!!

687
00:47:10,665 --> 00:47:11,713
Oh my god...

688
00:47:11,737 --> 00:47:14,006
Someone! Someone please help!

689
00:47:52,222 --> 00:47:53,696
<i>Seven years passed from that day</i>

690
00:47:53,696 --> 00:47:56,318
<i>Times are changing,
the Victorian era’s flying by us</i>

691
00:47:56,319 --> 00:47:58,541
<i>Population increasing to
the point of overflowing</i>

692
00:47:58,542 --> 00:48:00,796
<i>Art and entertainment
are showered in praise</i>

693
00:48:00,797 --> 00:48:03,649
<i>In the middle of this
unstoppable flow, agitation rages</i>

694
00:48:03,650 --> 00:48:06,150
<i>The height of development,
the growth of British culture</i>

695
00:48:06,151 --> 00:48:08,339
<i>But what goes up, must come
down. It’s only natural</i>

696
00:48:08,340 --> 00:48:10,231
<i>That the top runners are being singled out</i>

697
00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:12,238
<i>London’s peace has one
of its fingers broken</i>

698
00:48:12,238 --> 00:48:14,197
<i>Chaotic days mix the old and the new</i>

699
00:48:14,198 --> 00:48:16,174
<i>The map of London
paints a stark contrast</i>

700
00:48:16,174 --> 00:48:18,341
<i>Just like the current state of the country</i>

701
00:48:18,341 --> 00:48:20,063
<i>Put the focus on the
dark parts and you’ll see</i>

702
00:48:20,063 --> 00:48:22,253
<i>The curtain of swaying inequality</i>

703
00:48:22,254 --> 00:48:24,259
<i>In this market still
learning from its past!</i>

704
00:48:24,925 --> 00:48:28,551
You’re... You’re certain,
that it was the Stone Mask?

705
00:48:28,552 --> 00:48:29,842
The one excavated from Mexico?

706
00:48:29,867 --> 00:48:31,429
From Mexico, you say?

707
00:48:31,453 --> 00:48:33,168
It was quite a while ago...

708
00:48:33,169 --> 00:48:35,897
A while?! Could you please clarify?

709
00:48:36,451 --> 00:48:38,738
Yes, I’m <i>certain</i>, sir.

710
00:48:38,739 --> 00:48:42,032
Some gentleman’s wife
fell in love with it,

711
00:48:42,056 --> 00:48:43,916
And bought it from me at a high price—

712
00:48:43,916 --> 00:48:46,724
Yes!! Finally! I found it!

713
00:48:46,732 --> 00:48:48,474
Now, where could I find this gentleman—

714
00:48:48,478 --> 00:48:49,478
Wait a minute!

715
00:48:49,835 --> 00:48:51,160
I don’t trust you...

716
00:48:51,446 --> 00:48:53,743
Who the hell are you anyway?

717
00:48:53,793 --> 00:48:58,848
I apologise. My name
is Zeppeli, and I’m a baron.

718
00:48:58,849 --> 00:49:01,351
I came from Italy to
 find the Stone Mask.

719
00:49:01,352 --> 00:49:02,497
All the way from Italy?!

720
00:49:02,498 --> 00:49:03,165
Yes.

721
00:49:03,188 --> 00:49:05,283
Wait, he said he was
a nobleman from up north...

722
00:49:05,283 --> 00:49:07,402
I’ll go check in the books!

723
00:49:07,402 --> 00:49:08,402
Thank you.

724
00:49:10,448 --> 00:49:12,855
Just a little word of warning...

725
00:49:13,148 --> 00:49:15,198
The sun will be setting soon.

726
00:49:15,856 --> 00:49:18,502
It’s better if you don’t
go beyond that street.

727
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:25,175
A fog has rolled in...

728
00:49:26,329 --> 00:49:30,287
<i>(A palpable shadow stretches over the city)
</i>

729
00:49:30,287 --> 00:49:33,716
<i>(And soon it’ll swallow the sun whole)</i>

730
00:49:33,893 --> 00:49:41,701
<i>(Don’t let it get you,
fight as hard as you can!)</i>

731
00:49:41,702 --> 00:49:49,532
<i>(Fog and smog cover the city,
hiding the smell of crime)</i>

732
00:49:49,533 --> 00:49:56,296
<i>(Stretch out your hands towards the light)</i>

733
00:49:56,583 --> 00:49:58,448
<i>(We won’t sink down to hell!)</i>

734
00:50:01,782 --> 00:50:09,427
<i>The filth rubs off on the clean
and gathers like grime</i>

735
00:50:09,610 --> 00:50:13,436
<i>Thrown away with the rubbish</i>

736
00:50:13,437 --> 00:50:17,093
<i>Pressed together, our
lot gives off a stench</i>

737
00:50:17,093 --> 00:50:20,784
<i>The sweet smell of darkness</i>

738
00:50:20,784 --> 00:50:24,393
<i>Is comforting to us</i>

739
00:50:24,848 --> 00:50:32,474
<i>(Something’s wrong, people
 are thirsty, distorted, broken!)</i>

740
00:50:32,475 --> 00:50:39,816
<i>(Jack the Ripper has drawn first blood!)</i>

741
00:50:40,266 --> 00:50:47,809
<i>(Hate the poor, hate the
rich, and raise your voice)</i>

742
00:50:48,002 --> 00:50:54,627
<i>(Gather here and now, Jacks of this town!)</i>

743
00:50:55,105 --> 00:50:56,986
<i>(Rebellion is now!)</i>

744
00:50:59,806 --> 00:51:02,481
<i>In 1887, in Trafalgar Square</i>

745
00:51:02,481 --> 00:51:03,974
<i>(We raise our voices!)</i>

746
00:51:03,974 --> 00:51:06,739
<i>(Give us equality! Work! And money!)</i>

747
00:51:07,958 --> 00:51:09,796
<i>The rich in their ivory towers</i>

748
00:51:09,797 --> 00:51:11,713
<i>(They look on at us and laugh!)</i>

749
00:51:11,736 --> 00:51:14,835
<i>(Give us food! Every day! Let us live!)</i>

750
00:51:15,336 --> 00:51:18,638
<i>(The world is ever accelerating)</i>

751
00:51:18,670 --> 00:51:22,015
<i>Rebellion is stopped in its tracks,
blood floods the streets of London</i>

752
00:51:22,286 --> 00:51:25,611
<i>Away from there now, in Liverpool,
seven years have flown by</i>

753
00:51:25,612 --> 00:51:26,874
<i>Their graduation year</i>

754
00:51:26,874 --> 00:51:29,285
<i>Their graduation? But who are “they”?</i>

755
00:51:29,286 --> 00:51:31,367
<i>From inside the scrum
they head for victory</i>

756
00:51:31,368 --> 00:51:35,109
<i>So dazzling, brightly
shining, a pair of stars</i>

757
00:51:35,110 --> 00:51:43,160
<i>(Now is the time to raise our voices!)</i>

758
00:51:43,587 --> 00:51:44,840
He’s got it!

759
00:51:44,840 --> 00:51:50,720
The star of Hugh Hudson, our very
own Jonathan Joestar, grabs the pass!

760
00:51:51,993 --> 00:51:54,078
<i>(He’s like a heavy locomotive!)</i>

761
00:51:53,406 --> 00:51:54,506
{\an8}<i>(One’s on his back!)</i>

762
00:51:54,078 --> 00:51:56,258
<i>(He can’t be toppled)</i>

763
00:51:55,302 --> 00:51:56,402
{\an8}<i>(And a second!)</i>

764
00:51:56,259 --> 00:51:59,369
<i>(Keep pushing forward, JoJo!)</i>

765
00:51:57,946 --> 00:51:59,324
{\an8}<i>(Bloody hell!)</i>

766
00:51:59,376 --> 00:52:01,662
<i>(The pride of our school!)</i>

767
00:52:00,864 --> 00:52:01,864
{\an8}<i>(Incredible!)</i>

768
00:52:01,662 --> 00:52:03,581
<i>(Hugh Hudson’s acclaimed JoJo!)</i>

769
00:52:02,665 --> 00:52:03,744
{\an8}<i>(And a fourth!)</i>

770
00:52:03,581 --> 00:52:05,706
<i>(Is he finally wavering?)</i>

771
00:52:05,707 --> 00:52:07,139
{\an8}Someone caught the pass!

772
00:52:06,374 --> 00:52:09,156
<i>(None other than the great star Dio)</i>

773
00:52:08,350 --> 00:52:09,758
{\an8}<i>(Dio Brando)</i>

774
00:52:09,187 --> 00:52:10,536
<i>(Leaving them all behind)</i>

775
00:52:10,537 --> 00:52:13,177
<i>(Once again, Dio catches the pass)</i>

776
00:52:12,607 --> 00:52:14,189
{\an8}<i>(Nobody can catch up to him)</i>

777
00:52:14,118 --> 00:52:17,603
<i>(They move like clockwork! You’d
almost feel bad for their rivals!)</i>

778
00:52:17,627 --> 00:52:20,625
<i>(Our school’s pride!)</i>

779
00:52:20,490 --> 00:52:21,286
{\an8}<i>(Truly!)</i>

780
00:52:21,286 --> 00:52:24,754
<i>(JoJo and Dio!)</i>

781
00:52:24,754 --> 00:52:29,264
<i>(In perfect harmony, they
make the best partners!)</i>

782
00:52:29,264 --> 00:52:33,063
JoJo! Your pass won’t go to waste!

783
00:52:33,555 --> 00:52:34,817
Try!!

784
00:52:34,817 --> 00:52:37,386
The final match of the
season ends in victory!

785
00:52:37,386 --> 00:52:38,068
Dio!

786
00:52:38,069 --> 00:52:38,665
JoJo!

787
00:52:38,688 --> 00:52:40,003
That was magnificent!

788
00:52:40,006 --> 00:52:41,987
It was all thanks to your pass!

789
00:52:42,283 --> 00:52:45,503
Let’s go and tell Father
about it right away!

790
00:52:46,391 --> 00:52:47,217
Right, JoJo?

791
00:52:47,217 --> 00:52:47,876
Uh-huh.

792
00:52:47,922 --> 00:52:49,224
Dio!

793
00:52:49,248 --> 00:52:53,072
Can we write about your friendship
with JoJo for the school newspaper?

794
00:52:53,072 --> 00:52:54,072
Thanks!

795
00:52:55,001 --> 00:52:56,898
Let me get changed first.

796
00:52:56,898 --> 00:52:57,807
Shall we go home together?

797
00:52:57,832 --> 00:52:58,731
Yeah.

798
00:53:02,158 --> 00:53:07,597
<i>Time passed like the
endless flow of water</i>

799
00:53:08,183 --> 00:53:14,938
<i>Ever since you started
calling him “Father”</i>

800
00:53:16,228 --> 00:53:21,644
<i>I think of that word
which is so familiar to me</i>

801
00:53:22,366 --> 00:53:28,699
<i>Seven years spent studying diligently</i>

802
00:53:29,025 --> 00:53:35,759
<i>You’re... beautiful,
and a true gentleman</i>

803
00:53:36,487 --> 00:53:42,165
<i>My friend, who’s always
pushing me to be better</i>

804
00:53:42,858 --> 00:53:49,539
<i>You’ve repented for the
wrong you did to Erina</i>

805
00:53:49,903 --> 00:53:58,944
<i>You’ve offered me a shoulder
to lean on, now that Danny’s gone</i>

806
00:54:00,261 --> 00:54:05,476
<i>We walked this path
together for seven years</i>

807
00:54:05,476 --> 00:54:09,674
<i>I always followed in your
footsteps, one step behind,</i>

808
00:54:09,831 --> 00:54:21,606
<i>So why is it that I don’t
feel any friendship for you?</i>

809
00:54:38,342 --> 00:54:40,523
How are you feeling?

810
00:54:42,437 --> 00:54:47,239
Well, I’m old enough now that
a mere cold can last a long time.

811
00:54:47,239 --> 00:54:49,303
Sir, you’re not that old yet!

812
00:54:51,105 --> 00:54:54,907
Ah, well! I’ve got some big news for you!

813
00:54:54,908 --> 00:54:57,564
JoJo and Dio Brando, they...

814
00:54:57,720 --> 00:54:59,763
Seem to have won!

815
00:55:02,502 --> 00:55:08,237
Ah, Dio is a proper member
of the Joestar family now!

816
00:55:10,056 --> 00:55:13,322
And JoJo has become
a splendid gentleman.

817
00:55:13,322 --> 00:55:16,893
His recent archaeology thesis is superb!

818
00:55:17,345 --> 00:55:21,800
And Dio is projected to graduate
top of his class in law school.

819
00:55:22,494 --> 00:55:23,494
I...

820
00:55:24,030 --> 00:55:25,902
I admire you! Back then—

821
00:55:25,929 --> 00:55:26,947
My lord!

822
00:55:27,214 --> 00:55:27,602
Yes?

823
00:55:27,626 --> 00:55:28,921
I’m home!

824
00:55:29,309 --> 00:55:32,985
Dio! Welcome back!
Ah, and JoJo as well!

825
00:55:34,403 --> 00:55:35,403
Father!

826
00:55:35,706 --> 00:55:36,846
Are you alright?

827
00:55:38,268 --> 00:55:40,595
I can’t get rid of this cough...

828
00:55:41,181 --> 00:55:44,928
Today, the doctor recommended
I be admitted to hospital.

829
00:55:47,158 --> 00:55:48,458
I object!

830
00:55:50,832 --> 00:55:54,284
These days, hospitals
only care about profits!

831
00:55:54,697 --> 00:55:56,569
They say it’s a problem in London too.

832
00:55:57,592 --> 00:55:58,592
It’s true...

833
00:55:58,868 --> 00:56:01,237
I feel safer at home.

834
00:56:02,024 --> 00:56:03,261
I give in.

835
00:56:04,373 --> 00:56:09,010
The shaky hands and chest pain,
they’ll likely get better before long.

836
00:56:10,055 --> 00:56:13,324
Enough of that. You two...
Congratulations on your victory!

837
00:56:13,340 --> 00:56:13,710
What?!

838
00:56:13,743 --> 00:56:14,205
What?!

839
00:56:14,229 --> 00:56:15,259
You already know?

840
00:56:15,283 --> 00:56:16,316
How?

841
00:56:16,340 --> 00:56:19,222
Inspector Archer here told me.

842
00:56:19,475 --> 00:56:20,801
How rude of you, inspector!

843
00:56:20,806 --> 00:56:21,306
Huh?

844
00:56:22,132 --> 00:56:23,293
We...

845
00:56:24,235 --> 00:56:26,963
We wanted to see Father’s face light up...

846
00:56:27,545 --> 00:56:28,704
So we rushed home!

847
00:56:30,250 --> 00:56:32,335
Oh no, silly me!

848
00:56:33,950 --> 00:56:37,407
I truly am proud.

849
00:56:38,302 --> 00:56:41,794
I have such wonderful sons.

850
00:56:43,829 --> 00:56:45,565
Especially you, Dio.

851
00:56:46,089 --> 00:56:48,251
You’ve worked so very hard.

852
00:56:49,146 --> 00:56:53,002
Feel free to do whatever
you like after graduation.

853
00:56:54,519 --> 00:56:55,987
I was born poor...

854
00:56:56,670 --> 00:56:58,440
But you gave me a chance.

855
00:56:58,995 --> 00:57:00,233
Thank you.

856
00:57:02,162 --> 00:57:04,510
Well then, I’ll be off.

857
00:57:04,992 --> 00:57:07,838
Inspector, thank you for always visiting.

858
00:57:08,643 --> 00:57:12,429
I have a busy night ahead of me, with
the likes of Jack the Ripper out there.

859
00:57:12,430 --> 00:57:14,877
But this is Liverpool!

860
00:57:15,093 --> 00:57:19,882
There are men like him without
any humanity everywhere.

861
00:57:20,292 --> 00:57:22,018
Now, if you’ll pardon me.

862
00:57:47,131 --> 00:57:50,146
The spring mechanism only reacts to blood...

863
00:57:51,086 --> 00:57:52,386
Who on earth made this...

864
00:57:53,148 --> 00:57:54,299
And for what reason?

865
00:57:56,252 --> 00:58:00,125
If I solved this riddle, it might cause a
sensation in the archaeology department.

866
00:58:00,125 --> 00:58:03,822
If that happened, this mask that my
mother bought would have a fate of its own.

867
00:58:13,599 --> 00:58:14,599
This is...

868
00:58:16,972 --> 00:58:18,207
Dario Brando?

869
00:58:18,726 --> 00:58:21,139
Thank you again, Master Dio—

870
00:58:21,140 --> 00:58:23,910
Oh, it’s the least I could do.

871
00:58:23,936 --> 00:58:27,817
Thank you. I’m getting too old for this.

872
00:58:28,684 --> 00:58:30,476
“Right now... I’m sick.”

873
00:58:31,515 --> 00:58:33,047
“I’ll probably die.”

874
00:58:33,984 --> 00:58:35,391
“My heart hurts,”

875
00:58:35,936 --> 00:58:37,109
“My hands shake,”

876
00:58:38,503 --> 00:58:40,229
“And I can’t stop coughing.”

877
00:58:44,609 --> 00:58:48,638
<i>Dio...</i>

878
00:58:48,971 --> 00:58:52,942
<i>Dio...</i>

879
00:58:53,343 --> 00:58:57,714
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

880
00:58:57,715 --> 00:59:02,320
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

881
00:59:02,653 --> 00:59:06,947
<i>Mum died and left me alone</i>

882
00:59:07,890 --> 00:59:11,088
<i>Yes, alone with that piece of shit!</i>

883
00:59:11,143 --> 00:59:15,721
<i>I endured no matter what</i>

884
00:59:16,824 --> 00:59:19,784
<i>Yes, until the day finally came</i>

885
00:59:19,785 --> 00:59:24,983
Bloody hell! Ever since that wench
died I’ve been crumbling in debt!

886
00:59:24,992 --> 00:59:26,209
I know!

887
00:59:26,476 --> 00:59:30,483
You pawn this crap and bring
me back some booze instead!

888
00:59:32,640 --> 00:59:37,364
<i>My one and only memento of mum</i>

889
00:59:37,364 --> 00:59:39,777
<i>You threw it away!
You wiped your feet with it!</i>

890
00:59:39,801 --> 00:59:41,460
I don’t bloody need it anymore!

891
00:59:41,467 --> 00:59:45,451
<i>He’s the one who killed mum</i>

892
00:59:45,452 --> 00:59:48,332
<i>Everything’s been
taken away from me</i>

893
00:59:48,363 --> 00:59:49,915
Are you bloody deaf, Dio?!

894
00:59:50,216 --> 00:59:57,773
<i>How hellish that your blood
is flowing through my veins</i>

895
00:59:59,198 --> 01:00:02,582
<i>I’ll bury you and this damn curse</i>

896
01:00:03,203 --> 01:00:06,018
<i>I will take everything
into my own two hands!</i>

897
01:00:08,063 --> 01:00:16,276
<i>I’ll stay on top, even to
the limits of my humanity</i>

898
01:00:16,791 --> 01:00:20,830
<i>I will find the resolve, plan ahead,</i>

899
01:00:22,206 --> 01:00:25,034
<i>And then, hiding behind a mask—</i>

900
01:00:25,034 --> 01:00:28,237
<i>Dario Brando, my wretched father</i>

901
01:00:28,763 --> 01:00:32,285
<i>May you rot in hell,
together with the past</i>

902
01:00:33,524 --> 01:00:36,646
<i>A world where everything is perfect,</i>

903
01:00:37,503 --> 01:00:41,317
<i>In the palm of your hand, Dio!</i>

904
01:00:50,992 --> 01:00:51,992
Dio!

905
01:00:53,261 --> 01:00:54,830
What’s that in your hand? Medicine?

906
01:00:57,466 --> 01:00:58,688
What’s the matter, JoJo?

907
01:00:58,688 --> 01:01:01,019
I found this letter from your
father, from seven years ago.

908
01:01:02,577 --> 01:01:06,402
It details your father’s symptoms
at the time of his death.

909
01:01:07,479 --> 01:01:08,479
Huh?

910
01:01:09,001 --> 01:01:10,152
Show me that.

911
01:01:10,908 --> 01:01:12,715
They’re the same symptoms as my father’s.

912
01:01:15,890 --> 01:01:18,120
Are you always the one who
brings Father his medicine?

913
01:01:19,292 --> 01:01:20,190
What is this non—

914
01:01:20,191 --> 01:01:21,191
Answer me!

915
01:01:22,213 --> 01:01:24,126
What on earth are
you trying to say?!

916
01:01:24,126 --> 01:01:26,062
I’m going to have this
medicine investigated.

917
01:01:28,775 --> 01:01:29,775
JoJo...

918
01:01:31,410 --> 01:01:33,603
If you doubt the validity
of that medicine,

919
01:01:33,603 --> 01:01:36,239
Then you doubt our very friendship.

920
01:01:37,122 --> 01:01:38,122
Dio,

921
01:01:38,852 --> 01:01:40,304
As a gentleman,

922
01:01:40,312 --> 01:01:43,549
I ask you to swear your innocence on
your father’s honour and the Brando name.

923
01:01:44,755 --> 01:01:46,746
If you can swear on your father’s honour,

924
01:01:47,072 --> 01:01:48,770
I’ll never speak of this again.

925
01:01:48,985 --> 01:01:50,987
Swear on that guy?

926
01:01:51,835 --> 01:01:52,835
Dio,

927
01:01:53,039 --> 01:01:53,795
Swear on it.

928
01:01:53,795 --> 01:01:55,539
DIO: Swear on it?
JOJO: Come on, swear on it!

929
01:01:55,540 --> 01:01:57,088
DIO: Swear...
JOJO: Swear on it now!

930
01:01:57,089 --> 01:01:58,478
DIO: Swear...
JOJO: Can you swear on it, Dio?!

931
01:01:58,479 --> 01:02:01,219
That scum has never had any
honour for me to swear on!

932
01:02:01,723 --> 01:02:03,432
Give me the medicine back!

933
01:02:10,956 --> 01:02:13,390
I won’t ever let you go
near my father again!

934
01:02:14,099 --> 01:02:15,295
I’m convinced now...

935
01:02:16,035 --> 01:02:18,438
That there was never any
friendship between us to begin with!

936
01:02:19,375 --> 01:02:21,716
I’ll protect the Joestar family.

937
01:02:21,732 --> 01:02:23,348
This is all a
misunderstanding, JoJo!

938
01:02:24,412 --> 01:02:25,706
Just a misunderstanding...

939
01:02:26,849 --> 01:02:27,949
Besides...

940
01:02:29,655 --> 01:02:31,116
It’s not like you have
any proof, do you?

941
01:02:32,362 --> 01:02:33,942
Nothing more than a flimsy theory.

942
01:02:35,339 --> 01:02:36,339
Yes,

943
01:02:36,624 --> 01:02:39,101
I despised my father, hated
him more than anything.

944
01:02:39,403 --> 01:02:42,282
I just lost my temper when
you started suspecting me...

945
01:02:42,606 --> 01:02:44,240
JoJo! JoJo!!

946
01:02:45,890 --> 01:02:46,890
JoJo...

947
01:02:48,405 --> 01:02:50,241
Is something the matter, Master Dio?

948
01:02:51,207 --> 01:02:52,207
No...

949
01:02:52,988 --> 01:02:54,289
I’m alright...

950
01:02:58,713 --> 01:03:03,194
<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

951
01:03:03,329 --> 01:03:05,795
It’s too late to turn back now.

952
01:03:06,830 --> 01:03:10,132
<i>A world where everything is perfect,</i>

953
01:03:10,605 --> 01:03:14,770
<i>In the palm of your hand, Dio!</i>

954
01:03:18,748 --> 01:03:20,216
Father!

955
01:03:20,216 --> 01:03:22,470
What’s going on, Young Master JoJo?!

956
01:03:21,444 --> 01:03:22,444
-Father!

957
01:03:22,470 --> 01:03:23,930
What’s all this ruckus for?

958
01:03:23,931 --> 01:03:24,948
Father...

959
01:03:24,971 --> 01:03:27,305
I’m going to London
for two or three days.

960
01:03:27,701 --> 01:03:32,154
While I’m gone, take only what the
doctors and nurses I’ve hired give you.

961
01:03:32,796 --> 01:03:36,342
Please don’t accept any care
or medicine from anyone else.

962
01:03:36,342 --> 01:03:37,519
Excuse me, but—

963
01:03:37,543 --> 01:03:40,137
We’ll do as he says.

964
01:03:40,959 --> 01:03:42,606
I don’t know what’s going on...

965
01:03:43,090 --> 01:03:46,235
But I trust my son!

966
01:03:46,671 --> 01:03:48,671
Thank you, Father.

967
01:03:54,960 --> 01:03:58,147
Seven years ago, this thing...

968
01:03:59,372 --> 01:04:02,184
It moved in reaction to my blood.

969
01:04:16,344 --> 01:04:17,755
With this...

970
01:04:20,774 --> 01:04:23,706
I’ll make it appear as if he had
an accident during his research.

971
01:04:27,552 --> 01:04:28,552
JoJo...

972
01:04:30,462 --> 01:04:32,515
Your own research...

973
01:04:33,105 --> 01:04:35,591
Will be the death of you!

974
01:05:00,103 --> 01:05:04,260
<i>Time’s nearly out, so I gathered
my resolve and took off!</i>

975
01:05:04,276 --> 01:05:07,526
<i>Turning my eyes to the stars
and praying for an antidote</i>

976
01:05:07,581 --> 01:05:11,684
<i>I headed for the fringe of
society, the East End of London</i>

977
01:05:11,709 --> 01:05:16,203
<i>Now I’ve arrived here
in this town steeped in mud</i>

978
01:05:16,228 --> 01:05:19,643
<i>Ogre Street, the place
where plagues are born</i>

979
01:05:20,083 --> 01:05:23,403
<i>Before my eyes lies
the underbelly of society</i>

980
01:05:23,427 --> 01:05:27,383
<i>But I have a reason why I must move forward</i>

981
01:05:27,422 --> 01:05:30,903
<i>Even if I were to lose
this right hand of mine</i>

982
01:05:30,957 --> 01:05:32,026
<i>I’ll look to the stars!</i>

983
01:05:32,027 --> 01:05:34,112
<i>At long last our meeting takes place</i>

984
01:05:34,114 --> 01:05:35,925
<i>There’s a scent in the air
and it smells like prey</i>

985
01:05:35,926 --> 01:05:38,211
<i>Sniffing you out through the
storm someone’s making his way</i>

986
01:05:38,212 --> 01:05:39,925
<i>It’s time for your
leader to take the stage</i>

987
01:05:39,926 --> 01:05:46,883
<i>(Ogre Street, we devour anything we can)</i>

988
01:05:47,938 --> 01:05:56,147
<i>(Ogre Street, here everything meets its end)</i>

989
01:05:57,871 --> 01:05:59,839
<i>Dunno what the hell
you came here for</i>

990
01:05:59,840 --> 01:06:01,921
<i>Bet you thought you
stood a good chance, huh?</i>

991
01:06:01,945 --> 01:06:03,931
<i>In a moment we’ll
devour all that hope</i>

992
01:06:03,931 --> 01:06:05,885
<i>This is Ogre Street and
we’re the ogres, duh!</i>

993
01:06:05,909 --> 01:06:10,013
<i>Got no problem with you bein’ naïve,
I’m just showin’ you the simple reality</i>

994
01:06:10,038 --> 01:06:11,903
<i>Hey hey hey,
how about it, rich boy?</i>

995
01:06:11,927 --> 01:06:13,883
<i>Want a taste of the
edge of this knife?</i>

996
01:06:13,915 --> 01:06:17,583
<i>We’re gonna strip you of all that you got
Put up a fight and your life will be lost</i>

997
01:06:17,612 --> 01:06:21,443
<i>This is Ogre Street!
Ain’t it obvious that we’d cheat?</i>

998
01:06:21,477 --> 01:06:23,375
<i>Us have-nots are gonna
steal your riches away!</i>

999
01:06:23,375 --> 01:06:25,828
<i>From your life to that foolish
heart—we’ll steal ‘em away!</i>

1000
01:06:25,913 --> 01:06:29,263
<i>Tail between your legs, you can
save your own skin by runnin’ away!</i>

1001
01:06:28,588 --> 01:06:30,088
{\an8}Is this guy insane?!

1002
01:06:29,939 --> 01:06:36,399
<i>(Ogre Street, go on and leave it all behind)</i>

1003
01:06:35,724 --> 01:06:38,724
{\an8}<i>I don’t care if I lose four fingers!</i>

1004
01:06:37,823 --> 01:06:43,756
<i>(Ogre Street, we’ll even fill
our stomachs with your life)</i>

1005
01:06:43,763 --> 01:06:47,683
<i>I came here for a reason!</i>

1006
01:06:48,035 --> 01:06:55,864
<i>You said you’re fine with
losing four fingers, hah?</i>

1007
01:06:55,889 --> 01:07:03,479
<i>(Ogre Street, why don’t we
put that resolve to the test?)</i>

1008
01:07:03,876 --> 01:07:07,863
Hold on! I only came here
looking for a poison seller!

1009
01:07:07,888 --> 01:07:11,763
Quit bluffin’! Let me have a
go at this soft little rich boy!

1010
01:07:28,864 --> 01:07:31,160
That’s the sound of blade hitting bone!

1011
01:07:32,074 --> 01:07:35,453
<i>Made the mistake of my life, pickin’
a fight with this fearless tough guy</i>

1012
01:07:35,454 --> 01:07:37,651
<i>Countdown to my final breath—</i>

1013
01:07:37,674 --> 01:07:39,674
<i>Three, two, one!</i>

1014
01:07:51,724 --> 01:07:52,903
Stop, everyone!

1015
01:07:54,612 --> 01:07:58,645
I, Speedwagon, won’t allow you
to lay a hand on that gentleman!

1016
01:07:59,012 --> 01:08:00,829
Why didn’t you kick me
with your full strength?

1017
01:08:01,361 --> 01:08:03,023
I came here for the sake of my father.

1018
01:08:03,540 --> 01:08:05,060
So in the moment I kicked,

1019
01:08:05,084 --> 01:08:07,696
I thought you must have a father,
or mother, or siblings too.

1020
01:08:08,935 --> 01:08:11,271
I didn’t want to do anything
to cause your father grief.

1021
01:08:14,252 --> 01:08:16,162
Tell me your name!

1022
01:08:17,917 --> 01:08:19,358
Jonathan Joestar.

1023
01:08:19,766 --> 01:08:23,154
Mr. Joestar, if you’re looking
for poison, that’d be Wang Chan.

1024
01:08:23,332 --> 01:08:25,649
Be careful, he’s a crafty one!

1025
01:08:26,373 --> 01:08:27,615
Someone bandage his wound.

1026
01:08:27,678 --> 01:08:29,916
I, Speedwagon, will lead you to his shop!

1027
01:08:29,960 --> 01:08:30,698
Why?!

1028
01:08:30,722 --> 01:08:33,578
‘Cause I’ve taken a liking to ya!

1029
01:08:35,837 --> 01:08:39,593
<i>(Ogre Street)</i>

1030
01:08:39,901 --> 01:08:43,761
<i>With your determination to fight</i>

1031
01:08:43,841 --> 01:08:51,864
<i>(Ogre Street, you’ve lit in
us a glowing guiding light)</i>

1032
01:08:51,864 --> 01:08:55,904
<i>(You, who have the courage)</i>

1033
01:08:55,935 --> 01:08:59,904
<i>(To see the stars down here in the mud)</i>

1034
01:08:59,929 --> 01:09:07,907
<i>(Light up the darkness with
your unwavering heart!)</i>

1035
01:09:08,629 --> 01:09:10,059
<i>Your refreshing sunlight</i>

1036
01:09:10,415 --> 01:09:12,083
<i>Brought me completely to my knees</i>

1037
01:09:12,169 --> 01:09:13,692
<i>This must be some
strange twist of fate!</i>

1038
01:09:13,716 --> 01:09:15,144
<i>Let’s toast—to our meeting!</i>

1039
01:09:36,513 --> 01:09:37,513
JoJo...

1040
01:09:42,606 --> 01:09:43,606
JoJo...!

1041
01:09:55,164 --> 01:09:58,414
<i>Dio...</i>

1042
01:09:59,328 --> 01:10:01,360
JoJo has gone off to London...

1043
01:10:01,645 --> 01:10:03,547
Could he have died a dog’s death already?

1044
01:10:04,084 --> 01:10:07,592
<i>Dio...</i>

1045
01:10:08,102 --> 01:10:10,452
Or could he have found
evidence of the medicine?

1046
01:10:10,766 --> 01:10:11,766
Which is it?!

1047
01:10:12,544 --> 01:10:16,225
<i>Dio...</i>

1048
01:10:16,830 --> 01:10:19,987
Booze! I can’t help but drink!

1049
01:10:21,225 --> 01:10:25,567
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1050
01:10:25,567 --> 01:10:28,403
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

1051
01:10:28,024 --> 01:10:30,135
-Shut up, get out of my head!

1052
01:10:30,136 --> 01:10:34,584
<i>You’re the only one I care about</i>

1053
01:10:34,607 --> 01:10:38,807
<i>Become the richest man!</i>

1054
01:10:37,024 --> 01:10:39,212
-You piece of shit, we’re not the same!

1055
01:10:39,672 --> 01:10:42,165
Watch where you’re going, twat!

1056
01:10:43,057 --> 01:10:46,003
Oi, are you listening, you stupid brat?

1057
01:10:46,003 --> 01:10:49,191
You should ask yer mum to hold
you by the hand next time!

1058
01:10:47,498 --> 01:10:51,768
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1059
01:10:49,405 --> 01:10:51,551
Didn’t you hear me?

1060
01:10:51,773 --> 01:10:54,465
Oi! You piece of shit—

1061
01:10:52,043 --> 01:10:55,575
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>

1062
01:10:56,535 --> 01:11:00,773
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1063
01:10:56,535 --> 01:11:01,188
You filthy old tramps with
no sense of personal hygiene...

1064
01:11:00,774 --> 01:11:05,012
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>

1065
01:11:02,247 --> 01:11:04,172
How dare you! You bastard!

1066
01:11:04,374 --> 01:11:06,308
What did you do to my mate?!

1067
01:11:06,563 --> 01:11:10,690
{\an8}<i>One man’s misfortune...</i>

1068
01:11:08,088 --> 01:11:09,511
I’ll kill you!

1069
01:11:10,888 --> 01:11:13,440
{\an8}<i>Is another man’s fortune!</i>

1070
01:11:12,666 --> 01:11:15,445
Interesting, this is a good
opportunity to try it out!

1071
01:11:14,255 --> 01:11:16,907
{\an8}<i>You’re my clever boy!</i>

1072
01:11:15,446 --> 01:11:17,089
What’re you mumbling about?!

1073
01:11:18,675 --> 01:11:21,189
It’s a live human experiment!

1074
01:11:22,356 --> 01:11:27,563
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1075
01:11:26,178 --> 01:11:27,808
JoJo!

1076
01:11:28,282 --> 01:11:31,767
I’ll find the answer to your
research myself right now!

1077
01:11:31,167 --> 01:11:35,582
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1078
01:11:37,615 --> 01:11:38,615
What...

1079
01:11:40,375 --> 01:11:41,375
What—

1080
01:11:41,812 --> 01:11:47,026
{\an8}<i>[AZTEC CHANTING]</i>

1081
01:11:42,948 --> 01:11:45,147
What is this light?

1082
01:11:48,490 --> 01:11:49,796
Was I hallucinating?

1083
01:11:51,855 --> 01:11:53,155
He’s dead...

1084
01:11:53,488 --> 01:11:56,609
The spikes pierced so deep into his skull,
it must have killed him instantly.

1085
01:11:56,668 --> 01:12:00,024
This mask is just some ancient
sacrificial torture device.

1086
01:12:00,672 --> 01:12:02,130
He’s not dead!

1087
01:12:04,497 --> 01:12:06,969
Fangs?! What is he?!

1088
01:12:28,077 --> 01:12:32,615
<i>I’m thirsty, thirsty, so thirsty!</i>

1089
01:12:32,677 --> 01:12:34,863
He’s sucking my blood!

1090
01:12:37,141 --> 01:12:38,304
His face is...

1091
01:12:38,646 --> 01:12:39,924
Becoming younger?!

1092
01:12:42,787 --> 01:12:47,683
I don’t want the morning sun
to be the last thing I ever see!

1093
01:13:03,626 --> 01:13:05,227
I was saved...

1094
01:13:12,824 --> 01:13:14,346
By the sunlight...

1095
01:13:16,854 --> 01:13:18,340
He turned into ash...

1096
01:13:23,753 --> 01:13:24,475
Ow!

1097
01:13:29,341 --> 01:13:30,441
So this...

1098
01:13:34,070 --> 01:13:36,261
Is the power of the Stone Mask.

1099
01:13:41,423 --> 01:13:42,984
So, where is Dio?

1100
01:13:42,984 --> 01:13:44,667
It seems he hasn’t come
home since last night.

1101
01:13:44,667 --> 01:13:46,016
I’ll call for reinforcements right away.

1102
01:13:46,016 --> 01:13:47,093
Please use the foyer.

1103
01:13:47,117 --> 01:13:48,021
Thank you.

1104
01:13:48,237 --> 01:13:49,217
-You there!
-Sir!

1105
01:13:49,234 --> 01:13:51,626
This Asian fellow,
Wang Chan—take him away.

1106
01:13:51,686 --> 01:13:52,473
Yes sir!

1107
01:13:55,924 --> 01:13:57,799
Oi, come on!

1108
01:13:58,993 --> 01:13:59,993
JoJo...

1109
01:14:00,532 --> 01:14:01,786
I apologise.

1110
01:14:02,095 --> 01:14:03,912
This is my cross to bear.

1111
01:14:04,633 --> 01:14:05,538
What?

1112
01:14:05,538 --> 01:14:08,983
If only I had made sure
that man was exiled...

1113
01:14:09,487 --> 01:14:10,577
Dio’s father...

1114
01:14:11,133 --> 01:14:12,601
Dario Brando.

1115
01:14:13,456 --> 01:14:15,003
What do you mean?

1116
01:14:16,241 --> 01:14:18,734
I’ll tell you about it.

1117
01:14:19,502 --> 01:14:22,871
This happened when you were a baby.

1118
01:14:24,319 --> 01:14:28,009
This is certainly my ring,

1119
01:14:28,256 --> 01:14:31,063
But I never reported a theft.

1120
01:14:31,072 --> 01:14:34,349
I arrested the man who
was caught pawning it.

1121
01:14:34,763 --> 01:14:41,143
Lord Joestar had that ring specially made
as a pair for his and his wife’s engagement.

1122
01:14:41,143 --> 01:14:43,020
It was obvious that it was stolen!

1123
01:14:43,369 --> 01:14:48,397
Yes, it’s the ring I had made with my wife.

1124
01:14:49,978 --> 01:14:53,602
When Lord Joestar thought about his wife,

1125
01:14:54,153 --> 01:14:56,037
Tears welled up in his eyes.

1126
01:14:56,618 --> 01:14:57,618
I...

1127
01:14:58,150 --> 01:14:59,664
I arrested the criminal!

1128
01:14:59,688 --> 01:15:01,112
Would you like to see for yourself?

1129
01:15:01,136 --> 01:15:03,454
Stealing from a noble is a heavy offence.

1130
01:15:03,454 --> 01:15:05,703
He’s certain to be exiled!

1131
01:15:06,464 --> 01:15:07,464
I see.

1132
01:15:08,140 --> 01:15:12,921
Here he is! Oi! Wake up! Brando!

1133
01:15:14,056 --> 01:15:15,053
Brando?!

1134
01:15:15,053 --> 01:15:16,324
Oh, bollocks.

1135
01:15:16,370 --> 01:15:16,926
Then that means—

1136
01:15:16,951 --> 01:15:19,995
Dario Brando isn’t some saviour,

1137
01:15:20,028 --> 01:15:21,393
But a thief!

1138
01:15:21,922 --> 01:15:27,035
Even knowing this,
Lord Joestar adopted Dio.

1139
01:15:28,946 --> 01:15:29,946
Why?

1140
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:31,160
I...

1141
01:15:31,749 --> 01:15:34,310
I was moved to tears by
what Lord Joestar said next.

1142
01:15:38,412 --> 01:15:42,584
Did he tell you...

1143
01:15:43,486 --> 01:15:46,743
That I gave him this ring?

1144
01:15:46,795 --> 01:15:48,787
Yes, he said that. A lie!

1145
01:15:48,787 --> 01:15:49,926
It’s not a lie.

1146
01:15:50,663 --> 01:15:53,795
This is what I gave him.

1147
01:15:54,368 --> 01:15:55,920
He is innocent.

1148
01:15:55,920 --> 01:15:57,923
But it’s a memento of your wife!

1149
01:15:57,929 --> 01:15:58,929
Mr. Brando,

1150
01:15:59,723 --> 01:16:01,232
This is yours.

1151
01:16:01,771 --> 01:16:06,578
With this ring, please buy
what you need for your family.

1152
01:16:06,578 --> 01:16:09,240
Lord Joestar! Are you taking the piss?!

1153
01:16:16,119 --> 01:16:26,662
<i>If I were suffering from poverty</i>

1154
01:16:28,135 --> 01:16:38,540
<i>I would have done the same
thing, yes, for the ones I love</i>

1155
01:16:40,208 --> 01:16:50,944
<i>When the stars in the sky
shine, they start to tell a story</i>

1156
01:16:52,187 --> 01:17:04,699
<i>Let’s pray that this light
will illuminate the darkness</i>

1157
01:17:04,831 --> 01:17:06,701
Thank you, sir!

1158
01:17:07,383 --> 01:17:10,872
You are too good-natured!

1159
01:17:10,872 --> 01:17:14,733
This scumbag will laugh at
you tomorrow morning!

1160
01:17:16,519 --> 01:17:18,113
That may be true,

1161
01:17:18,692 --> 01:17:21,541
But think about it the other way around.

1162
01:17:22,160 --> 01:17:32,343
<i>From the prison called fate,
people reach for the stars</i>

1163
01:17:33,978 --> 01:17:42,337
<i>Let’s embrace that courage,
that loneliness,</i>

1164
01:17:42,804 --> 01:17:46,808
<i>That pain</i>

1165
01:17:47,838 --> 01:17:53,593
<i>Everything is connected</i>

1166
01:17:53,593 --> 01:17:59,704
<i>There’s a meaning to it all</i>

1167
01:17:59,955 --> 01:18:09,703
<i>I believe in humanity
and all of its resolve</i>

1168
01:18:09,783 --> 01:18:12,132
I can’t see stars or nothin’!
That’s bollocks!

1169
01:18:12,211 --> 01:18:13,449
That’s why...

1170
01:18:15,060 --> 01:18:20,541
<i>I’ll keep on believing</i>

1171
01:18:20,758 --> 01:18:26,615
<i>That this gold I’ve passed on</i>

1172
01:18:26,955 --> 01:18:32,522
<i>Will shine one day</i>

1173
01:18:32,622 --> 01:18:37,094
<i>With all of my resolve...</i>

1174
01:18:39,456 --> 01:18:53,308
<i>I will defy fate!</i>

1175
01:18:57,357 --> 01:18:58,357
Inspector.

1176
01:18:59,949 --> 01:19:01,393
I’ll wait for Dio.

1177
01:19:03,452 --> 01:19:05,053
He can still be stopped.

1178
01:19:28,142 --> 01:19:30,957
I heard a bizarre rumour on the streets.

1179
01:19:31,632 --> 01:19:35,650
It’s said that a vagabond shattered
a wall with his bare hands.

1180
01:19:36,124 --> 01:19:38,249
And then...

1181
01:19:38,812 --> 01:19:42,724
When the morning sun hit the man,
he turned to ashes and vanished.

1182
01:19:45,255 --> 01:19:51,233
It’s the same as what
happened 30 years ago...

1183
01:19:52,300 --> 01:20:00,678
<i>It’s a wedge driven into
the wasteland of my memory</i>

1184
01:20:01,547 --> 01:20:10,652
<i>At dawn, a blood-red sun
rose over the Atlantic Ocean</i>

1185
01:20:11,486 --> 01:20:20,462
<i>Full of passion and yearning
for the unknown world</i>

1186
01:20:20,569 --> 01:20:29,471
<i>I crossed the seven seas
with my respected father</i>

1187
01:20:29,540 --> 01:20:38,180
<i>My beloved father, the voices
of my friends, my youth</i>

1188
01:20:39,186 --> 01:20:47,889
<i>The Stone Mask took
everything away from me</i>

1189
01:20:48,259 --> 01:20:53,012
<i>I swore I’d get revenge,
that I’d take it all back</i>

1190
01:20:53,041 --> 01:20:57,132
<i>Maybe not today, but
there’s always tomorrow</i>

1191
01:20:57,133 --> 01:21:00,537
<i>Yes, tomorrow...</i>

1192
01:21:04,343 --> 01:21:07,089
“A man is what he thinks
about all day long.”

1193
01:21:07,089 --> 01:21:10,478
There’s a saying that goes like that.

1194
01:21:13,053 --> 01:21:14,449
The Stone Mask...

1195
01:21:15,743 --> 01:21:18,920
If I don’t find it, I can’t
recover what I’ve lost.

1196
01:21:32,368 --> 01:21:33,889
I, Dio, was...

1197
01:21:37,921 --> 01:21:38,921
Shit...

1198
01:21:42,873 --> 01:21:43,873
JoJo...

1199
01:21:47,500 --> 01:21:49,865
I see you’ve returned from London—

1200
01:21:49,865 --> 01:21:51,486
I have the antidote now.

1201
01:21:57,794 --> 01:21:59,530
It’s a shame it had
to come to this, Dio.

1202
01:22:00,461 --> 01:22:01,776
It truly hurts me.

1203
01:22:04,480 --> 01:22:06,551
Although you might not believe me,

1204
01:22:07,979 --> 01:22:09,480
Those are my true feelings.

1205
01:22:15,438 --> 01:22:16,972
I understand, JoJo.

1206
01:22:19,224 --> 01:22:21,170
You’re honest like that.

1207
01:22:25,153 --> 01:22:27,011
Although it’s selfish,
I have a favour to ask—

1208
01:22:29,009 --> 01:22:30,423
The final one
I will ask of you.

1209
01:22:31,660 --> 01:22:33,494
Can you give me more time?

1210
01:22:34,861 --> 01:22:35,861
Time—

1211
01:22:37,792 --> 01:22:39,319
To turn myself in to the police.

1212
01:22:40,749 --> 01:22:41,749
Eh?

1213
01:22:43,644 --> 01:22:44,644
I...

1214
01:22:46,811 --> 01:22:50,090
R-Regret the choices I’ve
made throughout my life.

1215
01:22:54,019 --> 01:22:56,054
Because I was born into squalor...

1216
01:22:59,401 --> 01:23:01,607
My ambition was relentless.

1217
01:23:05,593 --> 01:23:07,362
What I did was terrible!

1218
01:23:10,386 --> 01:23:12,440
I want to repent for my sins!

1219
01:23:12,989 --> 01:23:15,936
Don’t believe a word he says!

1220
01:23:25,180 --> 01:23:27,923
I can see from your face that
you’re wondering who I am.

1221
01:23:27,948 --> 01:23:29,931
Allow me to introduce myself!

1222
01:23:30,453 --> 01:23:32,954
I’m Speedwagon, the meddler!

1223
01:23:33,667 --> 01:23:36,657
Growing up in the darkest slums,

1224
01:23:36,921 --> 01:23:39,168
I’ve met all sorts of horrible
people throughout my life.

1225
01:23:39,665 --> 01:23:42,431
So I can tell all I need to know
about a person just from their smell.

1226
01:23:46,504 --> 01:23:48,131
This guy reeks!

1227
01:23:48,131 --> 01:23:51,072
Worse than vomit!

1228
01:23:51,272 --> 01:23:53,138
He was born evil!

1229
01:23:53,162 --> 01:23:55,849
Mr. Joestar, you should call
for the police right away.

1230
01:23:58,306 --> 01:24:00,364
This man has confessed already.

1231
01:24:02,967 --> 01:24:03,792
Father...

1232
01:24:03,793 --> 01:24:06,287
I’ve heard everything I need to.

1233
01:24:11,033 --> 01:24:13,661
I will return to my bed to rest.

1234
01:24:16,142 --> 01:24:21,903
I don’t want to see my son
being taken away in handcuffs.

1235
01:24:23,135 --> 01:24:25,892
You won’t succeed in arresting that man...

1236
01:24:26,598 --> 01:24:29,271
He was born with an innate destiny.

1237
01:24:29,295 --> 01:24:30,295
Silence!

1238
01:24:30,597 --> 01:24:31,597
Come on—

1239
01:24:34,325 --> 01:24:35,883
JoJo, I understand!

1240
01:24:37,301 --> 01:24:38,699
Arrest me.

1241
01:24:39,729 --> 01:24:41,157
But, if it’s not too much to ask;

1242
01:24:41,380 --> 01:24:43,199
I want you to be the
one who handcuffs me.

1243
01:24:44,076 --> 01:24:46,168
For the sake of those seven
years we spent together.

1244
01:24:46,394 --> 01:24:47,394
Be careful!

1245
01:24:48,830 --> 01:24:49,830
Agreed.

1246
01:24:50,811 --> 01:24:52,300
I will handcuff you.

1247
01:24:59,231 --> 01:25:04,834
<i>To be human is to have limits</i>

1248
01:25:04,856 --> 01:25:10,422
<i>That’s what I’ve come to realise</i>

1249
01:25:11,359 --> 01:25:15,546
<i>And still the more I try to plan,</i>

1250
01:25:16,641 --> 01:25:20,664
<i>The more I see the limitations of this life</i>

1251
01:25:20,664 --> 01:25:21,664
What’re you talking about?

1252
01:25:21,688 --> 01:25:22,688
<i>You know, JoJo...</i>

1253
01:25:23,219 --> 01:25:26,501
<i>This frustration, it’s unbearable</i>

1254
01:25:27,209 --> 01:25:34,021
<i>I’m always coming up empty-handed</i>

1255
01:25:35,513 --> 01:25:44,419
<i>This prison I’m trapped in,
it’s slathered in mud</i>

1256
01:25:45,779 --> 01:25:50,591
<i>I can’t see the stars, and no
matter how hard I struggle,</i>

1257
01:25:51,136 --> 01:25:54,908
<i>My eyes are still blinded</i>

1258
01:25:56,130 --> 01:25:58,361
<i>Don’t you get it?</i>

1259
01:25:58,362 --> 01:26:00,702
<i>That murky sky up there,</i>

1260
01:26:01,198 --> 01:26:05,840
<i>It’s crushing me!
I can’t reach up this way</i>

1261
01:26:06,103 --> 01:26:10,591
<i>Yes, Joestar, even
your purest pedigree,</i>

1262
01:26:10,888 --> 01:26:15,066
<i>Can’t wash the filth out of mine</i>

1263
01:26:15,288 --> 01:26:17,362
<i>That’s why, now is the time</i>

1264
01:26:17,386 --> 01:26:19,616
<i>To break free, from this cage</i>

1265
01:26:19,616 --> 01:26:21,889
<i>And seize...</i>

1266
01:26:22,281 --> 01:26:25,312
<i>The stars!</i>

1267
01:26:27,647 --> 01:26:28,647
The Stone Mask?

1268
01:26:31,442 --> 01:26:33,010
<i>I...</i>

1269
01:26:36,623 --> 01:26:37,623
<i>I...</i>

1270
01:26:39,970 --> 01:26:43,018
<i>Reject...</i>

1271
01:26:43,942 --> 01:26:48,364
<i>My humanity!</i>

1272
01:26:49,088 --> 01:26:53,205
<i>JoJo!</i>

1273
01:26:53,230 --> 01:26:54,493
Stop!

1274
01:26:57,080 --> 01:26:58,226
-JoJo!
-Father!

1275
01:26:58,413 --> 01:26:59,413
Dio!

1276
01:26:59,966 --> 01:27:00,919
Dio!

1277
01:27:05,570 --> 01:27:08,636
Shoot him!

1278
01:27:08,901 --> 01:27:11,591
Shoot him!

1279
01:27:13,784 --> 01:27:14,878
Lord Joestar!

1280
01:27:14,878 --> 01:27:17,144
Hey—a doctor! Call a doctor!

1281
01:27:17,144 --> 01:27:18,753
Father! Father!

1282
01:27:21,525 --> 01:27:22,525
JoJo...

1283
01:27:25,713 --> 01:27:26,713
This is...

1284
01:27:30,957 --> 01:27:33,671
Your late mother’s ring.

1285
01:27:33,671 --> 01:27:35,897
A doctor’s coming, he’ll save you! Hold on!

1286
01:27:39,417 --> 01:27:43,625
Please... don’t blame Dio for this.

1287
01:27:46,802 --> 01:27:50,676
Maybe... the fact that
I was so hard on you...

1288
01:27:52,540 --> 01:27:56,684
Made him feel like I was
treating him differently.

1289
01:27:57,832 --> 01:27:58,832
Father...

1290
01:28:06,142 --> 01:28:08,241
It’s not so bad...

1291
01:28:10,473 --> 01:28:11,473
JoJo...

1292
01:28:16,750 --> 01:28:18,105
To die...

1293
01:28:21,442 --> 01:28:26,281
In my son’s arms.

1294
01:28:41,197 --> 01:28:42,197
Father?

1295
01:28:44,974 --> 01:28:46,623
How could this be...

1296
01:28:47,864 --> 01:28:51,472
I knew I made a mistake, back then.

1297
01:28:52,229 --> 01:28:54,734
Now he’s dead and there’s
no bringing him back.

1298
01:28:55,724 --> 01:28:56,968
Mr. Joestar...

1299
01:28:58,716 --> 01:29:04,284
<i>You always told me to be a gentleman</i>

1300
01:29:05,864 --> 01:29:10,517
<i>To always live with pride</i>

1301
01:29:13,248 --> 01:29:18,900
<i>Even though I said I’d save you,</i>

1302
01:29:20,700 --> 01:29:26,207
<i>Even though you said you believed me!</i>

1303
01:29:28,111 --> 01:29:33,614
<i>I couldn’t protect you—
How could I be so powerless?</i>

1304
01:29:35,483 --> 01:29:38,251
<i>What does it mean
to be a gentleman?</i>

1305
01:29:38,252 --> 01:29:42,449
<i>Father, open your eyes!</i>

1306
01:29:42,523 --> 01:29:45,527
<i>What’s pride worth now?</i>

1307
01:29:45,551 --> 01:29:48,122
<i>What’s the purpose of</i>

1308
01:29:49,548 --> 01:29:56,830
<i>This Joestar blood
flowing through my body?</i>

1309
01:29:57,745 --> 01:30:03,344
<i>You always remained a
gentleman, until the very end</i>

1310
01:30:04,952 --> 01:30:11,611
<i>Carrying yourself with
discipline and pride</i>

1311
01:30:12,316 --> 01:30:19,560
<i>Your resolve to shine a beacon
through the dark wastelands</i>

1312
01:30:19,909 --> 01:30:25,232
<i>I’ll accept it all, and
look up at the stars</i>

1313
01:30:27,278 --> 01:30:32,773
<i>I’ll engrave your will into my soul</i>

1314
01:30:34,482 --> 01:30:41,782
<i>Take pride in this heart
that shines like gold!</i>

1315
01:30:42,052 --> 01:30:47,167
<i>It will become the future,
sent up to the stars</i>

1316
01:30:48,507 --> 01:30:56,064
<i>This Joestar blood
flowing through my body!</i>

1317
01:30:56,166 --> 01:31:01,535
<i>Everything is connected,
there’s a meaning to it all</i>

1318
01:31:03,531 --> 01:31:08,856
<i>I’ll fight against this fate,
keep sorrow at bay</i>

1319
01:31:09,245 --> 01:31:15,549
<i>With just one drop of courage!</i>

1320
01:31:26,329 --> 01:31:28,130
Inspector! It’s an emergency!

1321
01:31:28,154 --> 01:31:29,017
What’s wrong?

1322
01:31:29,018 --> 01:31:32,144
The body... Dio’s body is gone!

1323
01:31:32,158 --> 01:31:33,245
What?!

1324
01:31:33,539 --> 01:31:34,638
What did you say?!

1325
01:31:36,492 --> 01:31:38,688
Oi copper, get away from the window!

1326
01:31:39,974 --> 01:31:41,767
Inspector!

1327
01:31:49,661 --> 01:31:52,185
What the hell?! He came back to life!

1328
01:31:52,186 --> 01:31:54,241
Even though we shot him into Swiss cheese!

1329
01:31:54,250 --> 01:31:56,845
Be careful! He’s got some kind of weapon!

1330
01:31:57,782 --> 01:31:58,782
Dio!

1331
01:31:59,105 --> 01:32:00,105
Stop!

1332
01:32:02,313 --> 01:32:05,310
Shoot him! Don’t just
stand there! Quickly!

1333
01:32:13,542 --> 01:32:16,944
I don’t get it! I can’t make heads
or tails of what’s happening!

1334
01:32:18,256 --> 01:32:19,976
JoJo!

1335
01:32:20,889 --> 01:32:25,419
Can you hear my voice?

1336
01:32:26,056 --> 01:32:27,586
H-He’s sucking his blood!

1337
01:32:40,023 --> 01:32:41,189
You’re—

1338
01:32:41,189 --> 01:32:43,971
JoJo...

1339
01:32:43,971 --> 01:32:50,878
I’ve gained such incredible power!

1340
01:32:52,049 --> 01:32:54,381
From the Stone Mask...

1341
01:32:56,024 --> 01:33:00,423
From your father’s blood!

1342
01:33:00,504 --> 01:33:01,504
Dio!

1343
01:33:01,563 --> 01:33:04,007
These monsters are
making <i>more</i> monsters?!

1344
01:33:04,031 --> 01:33:06,418
Run away, Mr. Joestar!
You’ll only get killed!

1345
01:33:06,418 --> 01:33:08,450
That monster is too bloody strong!

1346
01:33:13,988 --> 01:33:14,835
The brain!

1347
01:33:15,226 --> 01:33:18,706
That mask must have drawn out
an unknown power from his brain!

1348
01:33:19,438 --> 01:33:20,594
If that’s the case...

1349
01:33:22,025 --> 01:33:24,612
I’ll have to completely destroy his head!

1350
01:33:34,318 --> 01:33:34,927
Stop!

1351
01:33:34,951 --> 01:33:35,951
Speedwagon!

1352
01:33:44,121 --> 01:33:45,433
I must...

1353
01:33:46,994 --> 01:33:49,540
I must make my will stronger!

1354
01:34:04,492 --> 01:34:06,387
JoJo!

1355
01:34:09,553 --> 01:34:13,127
Weak! So weak!

1356
01:34:17,101 --> 01:34:18,315
Mr. Joestar!

1357
01:34:18,315 --> 01:34:19,370
Let me...

1358
01:34:19,370 --> 01:34:24,505
Let me enjoy this amazing power
for just a little longer!

1359
01:34:24,910 --> 01:34:30,355
After all, I still don’t know
what I’m capable of yet!

1360
01:34:38,316 --> 01:34:41,321
JoJo...

1361
01:34:42,300 --> 01:34:46,472
Stop this useless struggle of yours.

1362
01:34:47,965 --> 01:34:49,521
I told you, didn’t I?

1363
01:34:50,449 --> 01:34:53,069
No matter how many
tricks you come up with,

1364
01:34:53,773 --> 01:34:57,355
Humans have limits!

1365
01:34:59,765 --> 01:35:04,879
Quit hiding behind that
curtain! Come out here!

1366
01:35:06,064 --> 01:35:11,218
You and your friend
can become my lifeforce!

1367
01:35:15,584 --> 01:35:16,544
Dio!

1368
01:35:16,584 --> 01:35:18,529
This isn’t a “trick” I’m using to stop you!

1369
01:35:19,153 --> 01:35:20,200
It’s courage!

1370
01:35:22,640 --> 01:35:24,198
This fire won’t kill him.

1371
01:35:24,876 --> 01:35:27,435
Speedwagon, escape from the mansion.

1372
01:35:27,463 --> 01:35:28,463
What?

1373
01:35:29,024 --> 01:35:30,064
Mr. Joestar!

1374
01:35:31,074 --> 01:35:33,296
Don’t run upstairs!

1375
01:35:44,176 --> 01:35:49,499
<i>(The flash of flames,
illuminating the dark)</i>

1376
01:35:50,224 --> 01:35:52,793
<i>Come, Dio.</i>

1377
01:35:53,206 --> 01:35:56,230
<i>I’m up here.</i>

1378
01:35:56,586 --> 01:35:59,181
<i>Is that an invitation, JoJo?</i>

1379
01:35:59,181 --> 01:36:02,770
<i>Very well, I’ll take care of you first</i>

1380
01:36:02,806 --> 01:36:08,075
<i>(The flash of flames,
scattering the light)</i>

1381
01:36:08,989 --> 01:36:14,441
<i>I’ll put an end to you and
your cursed powers here!</i>

1382
01:36:14,465 --> 01:36:16,626
<i>It’s useless! Useless! Useless!</i>

1383
01:36:16,666 --> 01:36:21,387
<i>I’ll suck you dry!</i>

1384
01:36:21,412 --> 01:36:24,158
<i>(The flames are pulsing)</i>

1385
01:36:24,530 --> 01:36:30,684
<i>JOJO: Father! I’ll mourn you
DIO: I offer you my thanks</i>

1386
01:36:26,576 --> 01:36:30,398
{\an8}<i>(Flickering from light to dark)</i>

1387
01:36:30,684 --> 01:36:35,410
<i>JOJO: Please give me strength
DIO: For giving me strength</i>

1388
01:36:35,410 --> 01:36:39,796
<i>I always walked in your shadow</i>

1389
01:36:39,797 --> 01:36:43,870
<i>You were always right behind me</i>

1390
01:36:43,871 --> 01:36:47,583
<i>My youth was with you</i>

1391
01:36:48,014 --> 01:36:52,335
<i>It’s time for us to say goodbye to it</i>

1392
01:36:52,359 --> 01:36:53,359
JoJo!

1393
01:36:53,473 --> 01:36:56,840
<i>The Joestar manor is burning</i>

1394
01:36:56,864 --> 01:36:58,864
<i>And Father is dead!</i>

1395
01:36:59,697 --> 01:37:05,332
<i>I’ve lost everything, save for my life</i>

1396
01:37:05,904 --> 01:37:11,888
<i>I’ll let that burn to ash too.
I’ll stop you, Dio!</i>

1397
01:37:22,134 --> 01:37:25,253
Mr. Joestar was surely thinking,

1398
01:37:25,254 --> 01:37:30,911
That a stronger fire could overpower
that demon’s healing ability.

1399
01:37:30,912 --> 01:37:35,049
“If only the flames were
even hotter!” But by then...

1400
01:37:35,049 --> 01:37:37,940
The fire had already engulfed the
mansion, even overtaking the roof.

1401
01:37:37,952 --> 01:37:42,424
Damn it! Mr. Joestar!

1402
01:38:14,508 --> 01:38:17,137
This body is immortal.

1403
01:38:17,902 --> 01:38:21,513
The only one dying will be you!

1404
01:38:22,662 --> 01:38:27,003
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1405
01:38:27,003 --> 01:38:30,743
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1406
01:38:30,964 --> 01:38:34,886
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1407
01:38:34,910 --> 01:38:39,244
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1408
01:38:37,660 --> 01:38:39,160
-JoJo!

1409
01:38:39,291 --> 01:38:43,396
<i>I won’t let go of this knife,</i>

1410
01:38:43,397 --> 01:38:45,776
The knife you stabbed Father with!

1411
01:38:45,777 --> 01:38:47,793
It’s useless! I’m immortal!

1412
01:38:47,794 --> 01:38:55,705
<i>With this final bit of strength</i>

1413
01:38:48,728 --> 01:38:51,887
{\an8}<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1414
01:38:51,903 --> 01:38:55,609
{\an8}<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1415
01:38:55,765 --> 01:38:59,948
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1416
01:38:59,948 --> 01:39:04,506
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1417
01:39:04,513 --> 01:39:09,576
<i>This can’t be how my life ends—</i>

1418
01:39:09,609 --> 01:39:14,464
JoJo!!

1419
01:40:14,358 --> 01:40:15,705
Can you hear me?

1420
01:40:18,485 --> 01:40:19,785
You can hear me.

1421
01:40:22,040 --> 01:40:23,040
Good.

1422
01:40:24,244 --> 01:40:26,600
I hope you had a nice intermission.

1423
01:40:31,830 --> 01:40:35,692
I’ve returned in order to
continue telling our story,

1424
01:40:36,240 --> 01:40:40,780
Of the world to which all of
you have become witnesses.

1425
01:40:41,591 --> 01:40:45,136
And so that we can continue our
<i>show</i> of love for these characters.

1426
01:40:46,083 --> 01:40:48,689
I want the whole acrylic stand collection.

1427
01:40:54,728 --> 01:40:57,297
Just a few more until it’s complete!

1428
01:40:58,490 --> 01:41:03,871
I hope you get the merch
you’re looking for too.

1429
01:41:08,624 --> 01:41:13,013
Well, let’s continue where we left off.

1430
01:41:14,117 --> 01:41:18,852
The story up to this point
seems like a bit of a fairytale, but...

1431
01:41:19,077 --> 01:41:21,455
Make no mistake, it’s the truth.

1432
01:41:21,964 --> 01:41:26,874
Things are going to get more
and more bizarre from here on out.

1433
01:41:27,359 --> 01:41:28,359
Yes.

1434
01:41:28,692 --> 01:41:30,567
<i>Much</i> more bizarre.

1435
01:41:31,465 --> 01:41:35,828
Previously, the mansion was
shrouded in flames and burnt down...

1436
01:41:36,504 --> 01:41:39,519
But Mr. Joestar survived.

1437
01:41:40,346 --> 01:41:42,130
He beat Dio,

1438
01:41:42,782 --> 01:41:45,679
But lost everything.

1439
01:41:46,274 --> 01:41:48,820
Three days later...

1440
01:42:12,164 --> 01:42:13,337
I found it!

1441
01:42:13,361 --> 01:42:15,361
The mask that man wore!

1442
01:42:15,467 --> 01:42:17,577
If I have this mask—

1443
01:42:17,585 --> 01:42:20,613
<i>JoJo...</i>

1444
01:42:21,522 --> 01:42:24,584
<i>JoJo...</i>

1445
01:42:25,672 --> 01:42:28,513
<i>JoJo...</i>

1446
01:42:29,752 --> 01:42:32,960
<i>JoJo...</i>

1447
01:42:33,753 --> 01:42:37,896
<i>JoJo, can you hear me?</i>

1448
01:42:37,920 --> 01:42:42,403
<i>My voice calling for you?</i>

1449
01:42:45,703 --> 01:42:50,481
After carrying the unconscious Mr. Joestar
to the hospital, I came back to visit him!

