02:15:20,504 --> 02:15:23,710
<i>Get your revenge!</i>

1918
02:15:24,001 --> 02:15:30,318
<i>300 years asleep, haunted
by painful thoughts</i>

1919
02:15:29,136 --> 02:15:31,269
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry, we vow to kill!)</i>

1920
02:15:31,452 --> 02:15:33,705
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry, we vow to destroy!)</i>

1921
02:15:33,848 --> 02:15:35,940
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry!)</i>

1922
02:15:36,698 --> 02:15:38,276
Wait, Dio!

1923
02:15:38,397 --> 02:15:40,611
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry!)</i>

1924
02:15:40,707 --> 02:15:42,948
Come quick, JoJo.

1925
02:15:43,048 --> 02:15:45,183
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry!)</i>

1926
02:15:45,278 --> 02:15:49,269
My world is in the palm of my hand now!

1927
02:15:47,680 --> 02:15:49,521
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry!)</i>

1928
02:15:52,202 --> 02:15:54,526
<i>(Wry wry, we vow to kill!)</i>

1929
02:15:54,526 --> 02:15:56,869
<i>(Wry wry, we vow to destroy!)</i>

1930
02:15:57,091 --> 02:16:00,699
<i>I will dominate life at last,</i>

1931
02:16:01,154 --> 02:16:06,304
<i>Tearing its natural
order from God’s grasp</i>

1932
02:16:06,617 --> 02:16:09,974
<i>I will dominate history too,</i>

1933
02:16:10,085 --> 02:16:15,580
<i>Rewriting and upending it anew</i>

1934
02:16:15,896 --> 02:16:19,063
<i>I will dominate even time,</i>

1935
02:16:19,064 --> 02:16:22,943
<i>My body eternal and sublime</i>

1936
02:16:21,894 --> 02:16:24,759
{\an8}<i>(Eternal life!)</i>

1937
02:16:25,108 --> 02:16:32,942
<i>I will dominate everything,
rise above all my cares</i>

1938
02:16:31,204 --> 02:16:34,006
{\an8}<i>(We vow to steal them away!)</i>

1939
02:16:34,133 --> 02:16:38,594
<i>Win it all, negate righteousness</i>

1940
02:16:38,594 --> 02:16:42,407
<i>In this peacefully unaware country</i>

1941
02:16:40,239 --> 02:16:43,431
{\an8}<i>(This country is ours!)</i>

1942
02:16:43,580 --> 02:16:49,349
<i>I will dominate everything,
I’ll face them now</i>

1943
02:16:49,361 --> 02:16:52,684
<i>And demand peace of mind!</i>

1944
02:16:52,202 --> 02:16:54,318
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry, we vow to kill!)</i>

1945
02:16:53,407 --> 02:16:58,582
<i>My world, this world!</i>

1946
02:16:54,549 --> 02:16:56,687
{\an8}<i>(Wry wry, we vow to destroy!)</i>

1947
02:16:59,113 --> 02:17:00,256
<i>Wry wry!</i>

1948
02:17:00,256 --> 02:17:05,096
<i>This is Dio’s World!</i>

1949
02:17:13,453 --> 02:17:15,773
It’s melting...

1950
02:17:16,032 --> 02:17:18,209
It’s really melting away...

1951
02:17:18,209 --> 02:17:20,445
So much that there’s a hole in my cheek...

1952
02:17:20,668 --> 02:17:22,547
My tongue is sticking out of the hole!

1953
02:17:22,906 --> 02:17:24,571
Your cheek is melting,

1954
02:17:26,334 --> 02:17:28,968
And your tongue is sticking
out of the hole? Really, Jack?

1955
02:17:28,968 --> 02:17:29,682
Dio!

1956
02:17:29,682 --> 02:17:30,682
Oh, it really is.

1957
02:17:34,277 --> 02:17:36,327
The sun has set.

1958
02:17:37,666 --> 02:17:42,166
It’s time for your lives
to go down with it!

1959
02:17:42,482 --> 02:17:45,571
I’ve been building up my
courage for this moment!

1960
02:17:45,673 --> 02:17:47,743
Even so, I can’t help
this feeling of dread.

1961
02:17:47,743 --> 02:17:49,814
As a human, I can’t let
you get away with this!

1962
02:17:49,823 --> 02:17:50,823
JoJo!

1963
02:17:51,863 --> 02:17:53,569
Put your training to use.

1964
02:18:05,128 --> 02:18:08,332
<i>(We’ll feast! On your blood and flesh!)</i>

1965
02:18:09,175 --> 02:18:10,939
<i>(Steal it away!)</i>

1966
02:18:11,884 --> 02:18:14,545
<i>(To heal all of our wounds!)</i>

1967
02:18:14,570 --> 02:18:17,534
<i>JoJo, here’s a lesson for you</i>

1968
02:18:18,787 --> 02:18:24,142
<i>The north wind made the vikings!</i>

1969
02:18:24,221 --> 02:18:25,626
This battle will be an exercise—

1970
02:18:25,626 --> 02:18:28,652
You’ll defeat them without spilling
a single drop of wine from this glass!

1971
02:18:28,674 --> 02:18:31,593
SPW: We’re not here to play around, have you lost it?
ZEP: You shut your trap!

1972
02:18:31,624 --> 02:18:33,589
The north wind made the vikings!

1973
02:18:34,486 --> 02:18:37,427
JACK: I’ll kill them!
DIO: Ah—wait, wait—

1974
02:18:42,738 --> 02:18:47,174
<i>Tough vikings were born
from the harsh north wind</i>

1975
02:18:47,427 --> 02:18:51,233
<i>Will this wine make a viking out of you?</i>

1976
02:18:50,857 --> 02:18:51,998
{\an8}<i>(Give us your blood!)</i>

1977
02:18:52,061 --> 02:18:56,593
<i>Make fear your own!
Here’s a battle lesson:</i>

1978
02:18:56,618 --> 02:19:00,992
<i>Muster up your courage! When the time
comes, don’t let your breathing go awry!</i>

1979
02:19:01,200 --> 02:19:05,041
<i>The hymn of humanity is a song of courage!</i>

1980
02:19:05,394 --> 02:19:09,731
<i>The greatness of humanity is
the greatness of courage!</i>

1981
02:19:09,910 --> 02:19:15,681
<i>Everything is connected!
There’s a meaning to it all!</i>

1982
02:19:16,146 --> 02:19:18,458
<i>Don’t let your breathing go awry!</i>

1983
02:19:22,247 --> 02:19:23,303
{\an8}<i>(Wry!)</i>

1984
02:19:22,461 --> 02:19:24,736
<i>This wine will be my north wind!</i>

1985
02:19:23,755 --> 02:19:25,170
{\an8}<i>(Give us your blood!)</i>

1986
02:19:24,774 --> 02:19:26,791
<i>The ripple of the wine!</i>

1987
02:19:26,106 --> 02:19:27,918
{\an8}<i>(We’ll feast on your flesh!)</i>

1988
02:19:27,406 --> 02:19:31,608
<i>I can feel it flow, I’ll find my
way through the darkness!</i>

1989
02:19:31,696 --> 02:19:34,036
<i>The waves of the ripple!</i>

1990
02:19:33,135 --> 02:19:34,463
{\an8}<i>(Give us your blood!)</i>

1991
02:19:34,145 --> 02:19:36,297
<i>Are resounding through my body!</i>

1992
02:19:35,400 --> 02:19:36,638
{\an8}<i>(We’ll feast on your flesh!)</i>

1993
02:19:36,424 --> 02:19:38,416
<i>With the power of the sun!</i>

1994
02:19:38,416 --> 02:19:41,199
<i>Find your way through the darkness!</i>

1995
02:19:41,230 --> 02:19:44,684
<i>Oh, my heart resonates!</i>

1996
02:19:45,134 --> 02:19:51,046
<i>Pa-pow-pow-pow with unrelenting heat!</i>

1997
02:19:49,185 --> 02:19:50,185
{\an8}<i>(Heat!)</i>

1998
02:19:51,112 --> 02:19:52,207
<i>Sunlight...</i>

1999
02:19:52,231 --> 02:19:53,364
<i>(Sunlight...)</i>

2000
02:19:53,364 --> 02:19:54,553
<i>Yellow...</i>

2001
02:19:54,577 --> 02:19:55,765
<i>(Yellow...)</i>

2002
02:19:55,767 --> 02:19:56,788
<i>Over...</i>

2003
02:19:56,812 --> 02:19:57,451
<i>(Over!)</i>

2004
02:19:57,476 --> 02:19:59,109
<i>Sunlight yellow, sunlight yellow</i>

2005
02:19:59,110 --> 02:20:07,813
<i>Overdrive!!</i>

2006
02:20:14,182 --> 02:20:16,656
The ripple of the sun! Dio!

2007
02:20:16,656 --> 02:20:19,164
This is the power
that will defeat you!

2008
02:20:22,751 --> 02:20:24,340
Dio Brando?

2009
02:20:24,372 --> 02:20:25,372
Yeah?

2010
02:20:25,758 --> 02:20:28,027
I don’t know you, but...

2011
02:20:29,067 --> 02:20:34,138
Let me say this to the Stone
Mask that awakened your brain:

2012
02:20:35,391 --> 02:20:37,408
Finally, we meet.

2013
02:20:37,728 --> 02:20:39,644
Don’t get carried away!

2014
02:20:44,856 --> 02:20:50,000
Perhaps you can heal this
wound in my stomach, JoJo.

2015
02:20:52,661 --> 02:20:55,293
You’re the one who put it there!

2016
02:20:55,946 --> 02:21:00,565
Then I’ll be completely healed from
the damage you dealt me in that fire.

2017
02:21:02,137 --> 02:21:04,597
I’ll be using your lives...

2018
02:21:05,041 --> 02:21:08,333
To purge this wound!

2019
02:21:08,334 --> 02:21:09,619
You bastard!

2020
02:21:09,620 --> 02:21:13,594
Just how many lives did you
extinguish to heal that wound?

2021
02:21:20,169 --> 02:21:28,833
Do you remember how many slices of
bread you’ve eaten in your lifetime?

2022
02:21:34,688 --> 02:21:37,204
I’ll make you submit!

2023
02:21:38,830 --> 02:21:40,609
By the ripple of the sun!

2024
02:21:41,764 --> 02:21:42,974
Pow!

2025
02:21:43,341 --> 02:21:46,627
Utterly pathetic!

2026
02:21:46,645 --> 02:21:48,422
It’s freezing?!

2027
02:21:48,515 --> 02:21:53,210
I guessed that this energy of yours
is related to the flow of your blood!

2028
02:21:53,210 --> 02:21:57,895
I am able to control my own body at will.

2029
02:21:58,993 --> 02:22:01,727
If I freeze up all of your veins,

2030
02:22:02,042 --> 02:22:04,929
Then you won’t be able to use that power!

2031
02:22:05,628 --> 02:22:07,771
I can’t—I can’t catch my breath!

2032
02:22:08,382 --> 02:22:09,601
Mr. Zeppeli!

2033
02:22:12,016 --> 02:22:14,805
Useless, useless, useless, useless!

2034
02:22:16,522 --> 02:22:20,077
Breathing techniques? Ripple?

2035
02:22:21,319 --> 02:22:23,995
If you’re going to be
blowing all this hot air,

2036
02:22:23,995 --> 02:22:29,220
You ought to use it to
play me a little fanfare!

2037
02:22:35,780 --> 02:22:40,121
Looks like your companions
are just as weak as you.

2038
02:22:40,122 --> 02:22:42,031
JOJO: What did you say?
DIO: Companions...

2039
02:22:43,367 --> 02:22:46,733
That’s right. Do you remember?

2040
02:22:47,117 --> 02:22:51,466
The story of the knights
your father told us that day?

2041
02:22:51,491 --> 02:22:52,494
What?

2042
02:22:52,532 --> 02:22:57,715
The tragic queen who was sentenced
to beheading by Elizabeth the First,

2043
02:22:57,824 --> 02:23:01,752
After a failed assassination
plot in the 1600s...

2044
02:23:02,238 --> 02:23:04,389
Mary Stuart!

2045
02:23:05,577 --> 02:23:07,417
It was about the ones who served her!

2046
02:23:08,085 --> 02:23:12,634
The story of those two proud knights...

2047
02:23:13,205 --> 02:23:14,182
Father told us...

2048
02:23:14,206 --> 02:23:15,206
Yes!

2049
02:23:15,519 --> 02:23:19,203
We listened to it together, didn’t we?!

2050
02:23:20,600 --> 02:23:22,812
JoJo, Dio!

2051
02:23:22,870 --> 02:23:25,539
I will regale you with
a tale of two knights,

2052
02:23:25,564 --> 02:23:28,210
Which has been passed down for
generations in our great England.

2053
02:23:28,970 --> 02:23:32,138
Those who lived with a gentleman’s spirit—

2054
02:23:32,139 --> 02:23:35,220
This is a story of knightly pride!

2055
02:23:37,133 --> 02:23:41,552
<i>Long ago, 300 years before today</i>

2056
02:23:41,729 --> 02:23:46,074
<i>Two queens battled for the throne</i>

2057
02:23:46,226 --> 02:23:50,612
<i>One was Queen Elizabeth the First</i>

2058
02:23:50,730 --> 02:23:54,847
<i>And the other, the beautiful Mary Stuart</i>

2059
02:23:55,183 --> 02:23:59,285
<i>Two legendary heroes came forward,</i>

2060
02:23:59,721 --> 02:24:03,205
<i>Offering up their swords to serve Mary</i>

2061
02:24:04,276 --> 02:24:12,373
<i>Tarkus’s strength cleaved
through rocks like butter</i>

2062
02:24:12,474 --> 02:24:21,466
<i>Bruford, with his skill and spirit,
cut down foes like a phantom</i>

2063
02:24:22,240 --> 02:24:26,788
<i>Without any family, the
two honed their powers</i>

2064
02:24:26,789 --> 02:24:30,908
<i>While wishing for a nest to rest in</i>

2065
02:24:31,200 --> 02:24:35,717
<i>After finding peace in Mary’s affections,</i>

2066
02:24:35,718 --> 02:24:39,968
<i>They swore their loyalty to her</i>

2067
02:24:40,412 --> 02:24:44,331
But one day, Elizabeth
accused their master, Mary,

2068
02:24:44,332 --> 02:24:48,494
Of murdering her husband,
and she was captured.

2069
02:24:49,457 --> 02:24:53,450
<i>The two heroes would not rest</i>

2070
02:24:53,708 --> 02:24:57,853
<i>When it came to saving their Mary</i>

2071
02:24:58,203 --> 02:25:02,633
<i>In order to stop those two heroes,</i>

2072
02:25:02,658 --> 02:25:07,065
<i>Elizabeth made an appeal:</i>

2073
02:25:07,112 --> 02:25:11,447
<i>“You two, surrender at once!”</i>

2074
02:25:11,613 --> 02:25:16,113
<i>“And I will spare your master’s life!”</i>

2075
02:25:16,113 --> 02:25:24,434
<i>This, we cannot refuse</i>

2076
02:25:24,475 --> 02:25:29,254
<i>In this, we hold no regrets</i>

2077
02:25:29,279 --> 02:25:34,458
<i>For our queen is our life!</i>

2078
02:25:34,801 --> 02:25:36,934
But in the moment they
were to be executed—

2079
02:25:36,958 --> 02:25:39,370
I’ll give you a little souvenir
before your trip to Hell!

2080
02:25:39,370 --> 02:25:41,860
Your master isn’t being held in the tower.

2081
02:25:41,916 --> 02:25:44,187
I cut off her head myself just yesterday!

2082
02:25:44,234 --> 02:25:47,513
Look at her lying over
there like a piece of rubbish!

2083
02:25:47,554 --> 02:25:52,100
After all, if she was left alive,
we’d risk a rebellion!

2084
02:25:56,699 --> 02:26:00,394
<i>You’ve betrayed us, Elizabeth</i>

2085
02:26:00,419 --> 02:26:05,295
<i>We curse you with our grudge!</i>

2086
02:26:05,740 --> 02:26:10,175
<i>We curse you for all eternity!</i>

2087
02:26:10,214 --> 02:26:14,674
<i>Stiff with rage, Tarkus’s
muscles were like iron</i>

2088
02:26:14,710 --> 02:26:18,814
<i>They couldn’t cut through his neck!</i>

2089
02:26:18,839 --> 02:26:23,674
<i>Bruford, filled with regret,
ensnared them with his hair</i>

2090
02:26:23,714 --> 02:26:27,073
<i>As though it were alive!</i>

2091
02:26:27,097 --> 02:26:29,160
<i>And that is the story,</i>

2092
02:26:29,161 --> 02:26:36,557
<i>Of those knights who lived
according to their hearts</i>

2093
02:26:38,859 --> 02:26:46,161
<i>Until the very end!</i>

2094
02:26:46,478 --> 02:26:48,171
Such blind devotion—
it gives me goosebumps!

2095
02:26:48,195 --> 02:26:49,805
Oh, what loyal hearts!

2096
02:26:49,829 --> 02:26:52,376
But those two should
have done a better job!

2097
02:26:52,401 --> 02:26:54,837
In the end, they couldn’t do
anything from down in the mud.

2098
02:26:54,837 --> 02:26:56,948
The only thing to call
their deaths is useless!

2099
02:26:56,973 --> 02:26:59,333
It might be as you say, however—

2100
02:26:59,358 --> 02:27:01,392
There is nothing that is without meaning.

2101
02:27:01,416 --> 02:27:04,520
The same can be said about the
fact that you came here to this house.

2102
02:27:04,750 --> 02:27:06,200
Everything is connected!

2103
02:27:06,200 --> 02:27:09,933
I want to believe that they
kept on looking at the stars!

2104
02:27:11,554 --> 02:27:16,032
<i>All people live in a prison called fate</i>

2105
02:27:16,057 --> 02:27:20,458
<i>Reaching out through those bars,</i>

2106
02:27:20,483 --> 02:27:25,141
<i>Do they see the stars? Or the mud?</i>

2107
02:27:25,172 --> 02:27:32,048
<i>Either one—</i>

2108
02:27:32,873 --> 02:27:33,973
<i>JoJo</i>

2109
02:27:34,997 --> 02:27:36,097
<i>Dio</i>

2110
02:27:36,912 --> 02:27:43,300
<i>Could be said to be correct!</i>

2111
02:27:51,625 --> 02:27:53,711
I turned those two

2112
02:27:53,942 --> 02:27:59,383
Into vengeful revenants that
would send even the devil running!

2113
02:28:00,229 --> 02:28:05,785
Even history bends before me!

2114
02:28:05,785 --> 02:28:06,985
It can’t be!

2115
02:28:15,429 --> 02:28:17,627
Such grotesque forms!

2116
02:28:17,628 --> 02:28:22,206
It’s the perfect form for
taking their revenge!

2117
02:28:22,818 --> 02:28:25,042
Don’t you think so?

2118
02:28:26,061 --> 02:28:28,681
Kill them all!

2119
02:28:28,911 --> 02:28:31,149
Continue from where
you left off on that day!

2120
02:28:31,181 --> 02:28:32,266
Tarkus!

2121
02:28:32,266 --> 02:28:33,289
Bruford!

2122
02:28:33,798 --> 02:28:37,087
Play me a fanfare with their screams!

2123
02:28:37,441 --> 02:28:40,100
Our grudge!

2124
02:28:40,101 --> 02:28:42,378
Our pride!

2125
02:28:42,379 --> 02:28:44,261
Great Dark Knight Bruford!

2126
02:28:44,586 --> 02:28:45,696
And you, Tarkus!

2127
02:28:46,439 --> 02:28:47,898
The way you feel—

2128
02:28:48,364 --> 02:28:50,564
Your pride, your resentment.

2129
02:28:52,675 --> 02:28:54,448
I can’t even imagine it!

2130
02:28:55,389 --> 02:28:58,580
But I also bear my own burdens!

2131
02:28:58,632 --> 02:29:01,712
I’m gonna be the one to eat ‘em!

2132
02:29:01,966 --> 02:29:05,216
I’ll savour every bit of his cartilage!

2133
02:29:08,748 --> 02:29:11,026
That man’s pride...

2134
02:29:11,027 --> 02:29:13,158
I will stand to meet it, as a knight!

2135
02:29:13,413 --> 02:29:16,027
My master—I, Bruford,

2136
02:29:16,222 --> 02:29:20,464
Would like to be the one to bring
an end to this brave man’s life!

2137
02:29:20,464 --> 02:29:22,599
Alright, go ahead!

2138
02:29:24,940 --> 02:29:26,496
We’ll duel as knights!

2139
02:29:30,142 --> 02:29:31,068
Run away, you two!

2140
02:29:31,069 --> 02:29:31,706
Mr. Joestar!

2141
02:29:31,729 --> 02:29:32,729
Tarkus!

2142
02:29:34,745 --> 02:29:38,015
I won’t let you interfere!

2143
02:29:51,821 --> 02:29:59,236
<i>A wedge driven into the
wasteland of my memory</i>

2144
02:29:59,503 --> 02:30:06,973
<i>At dawn, a blood-red sun
rose over the Atlantic Ocean</i>

2145
02:30:09,343 --> 02:30:10,230
Old man!

2146
02:30:10,231 --> 02:30:11,889
Don’t come any closer!

2147
02:30:17,960 --> 02:30:18,960
Damn it...

2148
02:30:20,626 --> 02:30:22,226
Fucking hell!

2149
02:30:23,665 --> 02:30:27,760
<i>There’s nothing I can do,
I’m a mere spectator</i>

2150
02:30:27,792 --> 02:30:31,499
<i>I’ve got nothing, I’m powerless</i>

2151
02:30:31,722 --> 02:30:35,460
<i>Come on, get real,
even at a time like this?</i>

2152
02:30:35,460 --> 02:30:39,654
<i>Even if I give up, the pain
will just be for another day</i>

2153
02:30:39,739 --> 02:30:42,646
<i>And tomorrow, yes tomorrow,</i>

2154
02:30:42,962 --> 02:30:48,052
<i>I’ll still be over here crying like a loser</i>

2155
02:30:50,137 --> 02:30:51,288
Honourable knight,

2156
02:30:51,836 --> 02:30:53,858
Is revenge your answer?

2157
02:30:54,303 --> 02:30:56,293
Is that what you take pride in?

2158
02:30:57,681 --> 02:31:01,242
If you want to preach, then fight
with your pride on the line!

2159
02:31:01,393 --> 02:31:03,460
You can lecture me after you win!

2160
02:31:03,484 --> 02:31:06,603
<i>Now’s the time, to let
courage resonate in my heart</i>

2161
02:31:06,603 --> 02:31:10,952
<i>I’m not scared of pain</i>

2162
02:31:10,968 --> 02:31:14,706
<i>I must find the strength to stand up</i>

2163
02:31:14,706 --> 02:31:17,635
<i>Tomorrow, tomorrow, tomorrow,</i>

2164
02:31:17,699 --> 02:31:19,926
<i>Tomorrow is right now!</i>

2165
02:31:20,005 --> 02:31:21,338
Old man!

2166
02:31:27,057 --> 02:31:29,426
Melt!

2167
02:31:29,692 --> 02:31:32,921
I didn’t follow you to
become a hindrance!

2168
02:31:33,145 --> 02:31:34,345
Speedwagon...

2169
02:31:35,374 --> 02:31:38,914
<i>I’ll let courage resonate in my heart</i>

2170
02:31:38,930 --> 02:31:42,915
<i>And look the enemy in the eyes</i>

2171
02:31:43,412 --> 02:31:46,880
<i>Won’t wait for a distant tomorrow</i>

2172
02:31:46,881 --> 02:31:50,750
<i>I’ll start walking,</i>

2173
02:31:50,750 --> 02:31:58,440
<i>Find the strength to
get back on my feet</i>

2174
02:31:58,924 --> 02:32:05,463
<i>Tomorrow is now!</i>

2175
02:32:05,575 --> 02:32:06,575
JoJo!

2176
02:32:10,081 --> 02:32:13,137
Cut finely, beat of my blood!

2177
02:32:20,619 --> 02:32:24,079
Please... This knight’s proud heart,

2178
02:32:24,080 --> 02:32:26,144
Let it somehow be restored!

2179
02:32:26,697 --> 02:32:30,421
I am the Dark Knight Bruford!

2180
02:32:31,203 --> 02:32:34,590
This pain means nothing to me!

2181
02:32:40,959 --> 02:32:42,608
Why aren’t you moving?

2182
02:32:45,912 --> 02:32:47,112
Just now,

2183
02:32:49,776 --> 02:32:51,296
You said “pain”.

2184
02:32:54,078 --> 02:32:55,328
That means that now,

2185
02:32:56,862 --> 02:32:58,449
You can feel pain!

2186
02:32:59,997 --> 02:33:01,060
Pain?

2187
02:33:04,322 --> 02:33:05,522
That’s why...

2188
02:33:07,558 --> 02:33:09,393
I stopped fighting you.

2189
02:33:12,590 --> 02:33:14,531
That’s why you stopped your sword.

2190
02:33:18,365 --> 02:33:20,237
You are a great knight.

2191
02:33:22,505 --> 02:33:23,805
You are human!

2192
02:33:26,979 --> 02:33:28,296
Pain...

2193
02:33:29,138 --> 02:33:30,914
Is proof of life!

2194
02:33:33,249 --> 02:33:35,898
So this is what it means to be human?

2195
02:33:36,891 --> 02:33:41,375
Because of this pain, I can also feel
the joy of being alive in this moment.

2196
02:33:51,899 --> 02:33:56,207
I feel a bizarre sense of peace now.

2197
02:33:57,901 --> 02:33:58,901
Bruford...

2198
02:34:01,845 --> 02:34:05,149
I dedicate to you the word
engraved in my sword.

2199
02:34:07,051 --> 02:34:08,586
Luck!

2200
02:34:09,741 --> 02:34:10,954
And also...

2201
02:34:11,209 --> 02:34:13,423
Pluck!

2202
02:34:20,478 --> 02:34:25,269
To think, I had to kill him
in order to save his soul...

2203
02:34:26,447 --> 02:34:28,973
Damn you!

2204
02:34:31,594 --> 02:34:36,813
JoJo!

2205
02:34:44,197 --> 02:34:49,293
I can’t believe you actually
defeated the Dark Knight!

2206
02:34:51,275 --> 02:34:53,297
Just as I thought...

2207
02:34:53,370 --> 02:34:55,457
I, Dio, will—

2208
02:34:59,188 --> 02:35:00,188
Hey baby!

2209
02:35:00,694 --> 02:35:04,083
I bet the blow from that
ripple-charged flower must hurt!

2210
02:35:04,170 --> 02:35:05,634
What the...

2211
02:35:05,745 --> 02:35:12,149
Your ripple is more vulgar than frog piss!

2212
02:35:16,639 --> 02:35:17,955
Watch out, Mr. Joestar!

2213
02:35:25,987 --> 02:35:28,606
What an embarrassment of a knight!

2214
02:35:29,265 --> 02:35:32,169
He never got his revenge!

2215
02:35:32,281 --> 02:35:35,256
What did he have to be joyful about!

2216
02:35:35,328 --> 02:35:36,328
JoJo!

2217
02:35:46,351 --> 02:35:47,515
No!

2218
02:35:47,986 --> 02:35:51,430
How could you!

2219
02:35:54,442 --> 02:35:56,192
For victory!

2220
02:35:59,331 --> 02:36:03,166
I take pride in victory!

2221
02:36:03,458 --> 02:36:05,197
Fuck!

2222
02:36:05,198 --> 02:36:06,642
I’ll get you!

2223
02:36:06,643 --> 02:36:08,109
I’ll get you for this!

2224
02:36:09,709 --> 02:36:10,709
JoJo...

2225
02:36:12,648 --> 02:36:13,648
JoJo!

2226
02:36:13,884 --> 02:36:16,027
My final ripple...

2227
02:36:16,755 --> 02:36:18,610
My... dying wish is...

2228
02:36:20,880 --> 02:36:24,777
That you take my ripple
and continue on, JoJo!

2229
02:36:40,950 --> 02:36:42,639
He collapsed.

2230
02:36:53,045 --> 02:36:56,733
I’ll vanquish your wicked soul!

2231
02:36:58,059 --> 02:37:01,678
Drown in the murk of history, Tarkus!

2232
02:37:08,816 --> 02:37:10,213
Old man!

2233
02:37:12,086 --> 02:37:13,086
Mr. Zeppeli!

2234
02:37:13,750 --> 02:37:15,036
If we lose you—

2235
02:37:15,037 --> 02:37:16,989
There’s no time to be sad.

2236
02:37:17,147 --> 02:37:19,609
The Stone Mask must be destroyed!

2237
02:37:19,830 --> 02:37:21,044
Old man!

2238
02:37:21,463 --> 02:37:22,463
I...

2239
02:37:23,256 --> 02:37:26,182
I lived my own life to the fullest.

2240
02:37:27,034 --> 02:37:28,518
In the end,

2241
02:37:29,193 --> 02:37:32,189
I leave everything I have to you.

2242
02:37:33,558 --> 02:37:34,558
JoJo,

2243
02:37:34,923 --> 02:37:37,327
You are my hope.

2244
02:37:44,444 --> 02:37:54,144
<i>Once again, life is
spilling out of my arms</i>

2245
02:37:56,044 --> 02:38:02,820
<i>You showed me my purpose</i>

2246
02:38:04,391 --> 02:38:06,390
<i>Who I am meant to be</i>

2247
02:38:08,347 --> 02:38:18,168
<i>You taught me that humanity’s
greatest gift is courage</i>

2248
02:38:20,137 --> 02:38:26,676
<i>The light you’ve given
to me will shine through</i>

2249
02:38:27,185 --> 02:38:30,380
<i>Into my spirit</i>

2250
02:38:33,128 --> 02:38:34,414
It felt like...

2251
02:38:34,414 --> 02:38:37,921
I had a friend and a son
in you at the same time.

2252
02:38:38,427 --> 02:38:40,156
From here on...

2253
02:38:40,736 --> 02:38:42,759
I live within you.

2254
02:38:43,630 --> 02:38:44,782
JoJo.

2255
02:38:48,627 --> 02:38:53,768
<i>Everything is connected</i>

2256
02:38:54,491 --> 02:39:00,010
<i>There’s a meaning to it all</i>

2257
02:39:00,732 --> 02:39:05,983
<i>That’s what I’ve come to believe</i>

2258
02:39:06,578 --> 02:39:09,553
<i>Even this pain...</i>

2259
02:39:12,513 --> 02:39:15,714
<i>Even this pain</i>

2260
02:39:18,481 --> 02:39:28,572
<i>My father left to me
what you leave to me now</i>

2261
02:39:30,425 --> 02:39:40,484
<i>The golden light that
shines from within me</i>

2262
02:39:41,311 --> 02:39:52,495
<i>It’s the one thing in my heart
that I can hold on to now</i>

2263
02:39:53,573 --> 02:39:57,954
<i>I embrace it tightly</i>

2264
02:39:58,965 --> 02:40:02,539
<i>And from this prison...</i>

2265
02:40:05,051 --> 02:40:07,519
<i>I see the stars</i>

2266
02:40:07,956 --> 02:40:13,783
<i>A golden spirit</i>

2267
02:40:13,980 --> 02:40:19,730
<i>Humanity’s glow in the darkness</i>

2268
02:40:20,338 --> 02:40:25,594
<i>Will light up</i>

2269
02:40:25,920 --> 02:40:30,100
<i>The way to you...</i>

2270
02:40:31,052 --> 02:40:31,986
Dio!

2271
02:40:32,034 --> 02:40:37,207
<i>Light up the way to you...</i>

2272
02:41:06,152 --> 02:41:07,983
JoJo...!

2273
02:41:16,523 --> 02:41:19,916
<i>Dio...</i>

2274
02:41:20,584 --> 02:41:24,020
<i>Dio...</i>

2275
02:41:24,772 --> 02:41:28,697
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

2276
02:41:28,976 --> 02:41:32,956
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

2277
02:41:32,981 --> 02:41:36,933
<i>I can’t hear you</i>

2278
02:41:33,334 --> 02:41:36,968
{\an8}<i>Dio...</i>

2279
02:41:37,408 --> 02:41:40,927
<i>I already killed my past</i>

2280
02:41:37,431 --> 02:41:40,970
{\an8}<i>Dio...</i>

2281
02:41:40,952 --> 02:41:45,183
<i>Don’t call my name—</i>

2282
02:41:45,287 --> 02:41:49,847
<i>You and I are different</i>

2283
02:41:50,050 --> 02:41:53,915
<i>We’re not so different, you’re my son</i>

2284
02:41:53,916 --> 02:41:57,955
<i>I have changed into something new</i>

2285
02:41:57,978 --> 02:42:02,178
<i>You’re not so changed,
you did it to survive</i>

2286
02:42:02,252 --> 02:42:04,258
<i>I’ll use any means</i>

2287
02:42:04,258 --> 02:42:06,393
<i>DIO: I’ll steal it all
DARIO: You’ll steal it all</i>

2288
02:42:06,394 --> 02:42:10,660
<i>DIO: Upend righteousness</i>

2289
02:42:08,518 --> 02:42:12,068
<i>DARIO: You’re my clever boy!</i>

2290
02:42:10,683 --> 02:42:14,800
<i>DIO: I will conquer it all</i>

2291
02:42:12,720 --> 02:42:17,173
<i>DARIO: What will you want next?</i>

2292
02:42:15,873 --> 02:42:19,346
<i>DIO: I will dominate everything</i>

2293
02:42:19,347 --> 02:42:24,211
<i>Go ahead and dominate,
what will you want after that?</i>

2294
02:42:24,235 --> 02:42:28,702
<i>What do I want?</i>

2295
02:42:26,808 --> 02:42:31,321
<i>DARIO: What do you want?</i>

2296
02:42:28,702 --> 02:42:31,273
<i>DIO: What do I want?</i>

2297
02:42:31,337 --> 02:42:32,978
<i>I want...</i>

2298
02:42:33,030 --> 02:42:37,060
<i>I want...</i>

2299
02:42:34,277 --> 02:42:43,033
{\an8}<i>Dio... Dio...</i>

2300
02:42:37,060 --> 02:42:44,441
<i>I want...</i>

2301
02:42:50,452 --> 02:42:51,881
So you’ve come...

2302
02:42:53,968 --> 02:42:58,253
JoJo.

2303
02:42:58,847 --> 02:43:00,126
Is this...

2304
02:43:03,632 --> 02:43:05,657
The world you wished for?

2305
02:43:09,223 --> 02:43:10,223
What?

2306
02:43:14,308 --> 02:43:15,308
The world...

2307
02:43:18,919 --> 02:43:21,677
That you’ve been trying
to obtain for so long...

2308
02:43:26,495 --> 02:43:28,394
Surrounded by death...

2309
02:43:29,971 --> 02:43:31,352
It’s a pitiful world, isn’t it?

2310
02:43:35,582 --> 02:43:38,822
It’s a splendid world where
I’ve dominated everything.

2311
02:43:39,268 --> 02:43:42,553
I’ve dominated death, and even history too.

2312
02:43:42,578 --> 02:43:45,590
For that reason, you stole
from uninvolved innocents?

2313
02:43:49,391 --> 02:43:54,089
They were a noble sacrifice for
the sake of the future that I designed.

2314
02:43:57,310 --> 02:43:58,572
You’re just afraid.

2315
02:44:01,287 --> 02:44:02,334
Of being human...

2316
02:44:06,572 --> 02:44:08,313
That’s why you rejected your humanity.

2317
02:44:12,833 --> 02:44:14,341
For the sake of obtaining this world...

2318
02:44:15,691 --> 02:44:17,340
I’ve <i>transcended</i> humanity!

2319
02:44:17,372 --> 02:44:18,592
You ran away from it.

2320
02:44:29,314 --> 02:44:31,446
The ends justify the means.

2321
02:44:34,386 --> 02:44:35,891
I will win,

2322
02:44:37,743 --> 02:44:40,985
And that means conquering
everything, of course.

2323
02:44:42,519 --> 02:44:45,181
All of this is fate!

2324
02:44:45,206 --> 02:44:46,356
No!

2325
02:44:47,773 --> 02:44:49,683
This is just how you
chose to live your life!

2326
02:44:51,366 --> 02:44:52,714
Opposing fate...

2327
02:44:54,532 --> 02:44:56,230
What will your legacy be?

2328
02:44:59,715 --> 02:45:01,650
Such righteousness!

2329
02:45:09,532 --> 02:45:13,117
Just like the one who gave me this power...

2330
02:45:14,817 --> 02:45:16,675
And then died!

2331
02:45:21,026 --> 02:45:22,645
Just like...

2332
02:45:24,677 --> 02:45:28,832
Your father.

2333
02:45:32,724 --> 02:45:35,072
That’s right.

2334
02:45:43,934 --> 02:45:45,914
As a gentleman, it pains
me to say this, but...

2335
02:45:49,092 --> 02:45:50,953
Now I, Jonathan Joestar...

2336
02:45:54,409 --> 02:45:55,897
For the sake of revenge...

2337
02:45:57,663 --> 02:45:58,663
Dio...

2338
02:46:01,091 --> 02:46:02,793
I will kill you!

2339
02:46:03,009 --> 02:46:06,925
We’re one and the same; you want
to exact your revenge! I admire that!

2340
02:46:06,950 --> 02:46:09,254
No! I’ve come to right your wrongs!

2341
02:46:09,278 --> 02:46:11,122
I’ve accepted this as my legacy!

2342
02:46:11,146 --> 02:46:11,849
Speedwagon!

2343
02:46:11,874 --> 02:46:12,587
Right!

2344
02:46:15,627 --> 02:46:21,858
<i>Ironic, isn’t it? Now
you’re the have-not, JoJo!</i>

2345
02:46:21,913 --> 02:46:24,946
<i>I’ll suck you dry</i>

2346
02:46:24,947 --> 02:46:27,427
<i>Become my next meal!</i>

2347
02:46:28,308 --> 02:46:34,360
<i>I’ve lost so many loved ones but
their light lives on in me, Dio!</i>

2348
02:46:34,589 --> 02:46:40,333
<i>I’ve come to cleanse
your corrupted ambitions</i>

2349
02:46:41,182 --> 02:46:42,933
<i>Useless, useless, useless, useless!</i>

2350
02:46:44,102 --> 02:46:47,013
<i>I obtained this power</i>

2351
02:46:47,245 --> 02:46:50,344
<i>My heart’s aflame</i>

2352
02:46:50,389 --> 02:46:53,558
<i>So I could steal everything from you</i>

2353
02:46:53,598 --> 02:46:56,598
<i>I’ll dull this pain</i>

2354
02:46:56,728 --> 02:46:59,717
<i>If you think about it, you’re just like me</i>

2355
02:46:59,758 --> 02:47:02,938
<i>You were just like me,
two sides of the same coin</i>

2356
02:47:02,978 --> 02:47:07,666
<i>Like fire and ice, my body is burning</i>

2357
02:47:07,690 --> 02:47:10,025
<i>JOJO: I’ll kill you
DIO: You’ll kill me</i>

2358
02:47:14,053 --> 02:47:16,005
<i>JOJO: You’ll kill me
DIO: I’ll kill you</i>

2359
02:47:16,617 --> 02:47:18,164
Just like Mr. Zeppeli taught me!

2360
02:47:18,315 --> 02:47:20,587
I’ll channel my ripple through this sword!

2361
02:47:20,588 --> 02:47:23,608
You did it! You defeated Dio!

2362
02:47:23,631 --> 02:47:24,957
Not a chance!

2363
02:47:25,250 --> 02:47:26,781
You fools!

2364
02:47:28,282 --> 02:47:29,837
What! The sword is freezing—

2365
02:47:31,860 --> 02:47:34,961
Utterly pathetic!

2366
02:47:34,961 --> 02:47:36,197
Mr. Joestar!

2367
02:47:36,495 --> 02:47:38,292
JoJo!

2368
02:47:40,799 --> 02:47:46,812
<i>Utterly pathetic! I’m grasping
your carotid artery, JoJo!</i>

2369
02:47:47,013 --> 02:47:53,013
<i>With this, you’ll become
one of my undead servants</i>

2370
02:47:53,417 --> 02:47:55,149
<i>Ironic, isn’t it, Dio?</i>

2371
02:47:55,174 --> 02:47:59,679
<i>Just as I thought, you were
running away from humanity</i>

2372
02:47:59,797 --> 02:48:05,013
<i>Why don’t you freeze me now, Dio!</i>

2373
02:48:05,924 --> 02:48:07,821
My fist... Just from hitting him!

2374
02:48:07,856 --> 02:48:11,116
I transcended humanity!
None of you are on my level.

2375
02:48:12,457 --> 02:48:15,613
<i>You’re nothing but a monkey, JoJo!</i>

2376
02:48:15,637 --> 02:48:18,761
<i>JOJO: No, for as long as I have faith,
DIO: Compared to me, Dio!</i>

2377
02:48:18,829 --> 02:48:21,669
<i>DIO: Let’s test your willpower
JOJO: I will reach you!</i>

2378
02:48:21,693 --> 02:48:24,893
<i>As long as we have faith, we can grow</i>

2379
02:48:24,918 --> 02:48:28,114
<i>JOJO: Us humans...
DIO: To be human is to have limits</i>

2380
02:48:28,138 --> 02:48:31,430
<i>JOJO: That’s what he taught me
DIO: You can’t reach me!</i>

2381
02:48:31,455 --> 02:48:34,414
<i>Like fire and ice</i>

2382
02:48:34,438 --> 02:48:40,538
<i>DIO: I’ll chip away at this body to prove it
JOJO: I’ll burn up this body to prove it</i>

2383
02:48:42,276 --> 02:48:44,120
He put his hand in the
fire! If he does that—

2384
02:48:44,145 --> 02:48:47,152
<i>Like fire and ice</i>

2385
02:48:47,176 --> 02:48:50,216
<i>My lost friends, my father’s spirit</i>

2386
02:48:50,426 --> 02:48:53,454
<i>Like fire and ice</i>

2387
02:48:53,478 --> 02:48:56,720
<i>JOJO: Our connection, it’s here
DIO: Even when I’ve thrown away my humanity</i>

2388
02:48:56,753 --> 02:48:59,660
<i>Like fire and ice</i>

2389
02:48:59,707 --> 02:49:03,429
<i>With my life on the
line, I’ll prove it now!</i>

2390
02:49:03,453 --> 02:49:07,634
<i>-Dio! Dio! Dio!
-JoJo! JoJo! JoJo!</i>

2391
02:49:10,819 --> 02:49:12,913
“I was only trying to be friendly!”

2392
02:49:13,311 --> 02:49:15,294
“I like being number one!”

2393
02:49:18,233 --> 02:49:19,272
“My eye!”

2394
02:49:19,304 --> 02:49:21,553
“I think my finger went in his eye.”

2395
02:49:25,734 --> 02:49:26,734
Dio!

2396
02:49:28,289 --> 02:49:35,713
<i>I won’t stop beating you
until you’re finished!</i>

2397
02:49:42,758 --> 02:49:43,913
This is impossible!

2398
02:49:44,457 --> 02:49:46,690
The heat is coursing through me!

2399
02:49:47,163 --> 02:49:48,414
I’m melting!

2400
02:49:48,438 --> 02:49:49,723
Crumble to dust!

2401
02:49:49,747 --> 02:49:51,961
I can’t be...

2402
02:49:52,961 --> 02:49:55,024
Not yet!!

2403
02:49:58,041 --> 02:50:02,254
Watch out! He’s shooting
hot liquid out of his eyes!

2404
02:50:02,279 --> 02:50:05,854
Lord Dio...!

2405
02:50:14,895 --> 02:50:15,895
Dio...!

2406
02:50:31,468 --> 02:50:34,198
<i>Extra, extra! Read all about it!</i>

2407
02:50:34,958 --> 02:50:39,403
<i>(In 1888 on December the 4th)</i>

2408
02:50:39,529 --> 02:50:42,013
<i>(The London Press reported)</i>

2409
02:50:42,013 --> 02:50:43,814
<i>There was a small incident</i>

2410
02:50:43,839 --> 02:50:45,721
<i>(In Windknight’s Lot)</i>

2411
02:50:45,721 --> 02:50:50,443
<i>(That little village, there was
a missing persons incident)</i>

2412
02:50:50,443 --> 02:50:52,443
<i>A very bizarre case</i>

2413
02:50:52,443 --> 02:50:54,625
<i>73 people vanished</i>

2414
02:50:54,719 --> 02:50:56,689
<i>In just one night,
they abruptly disappeared</i>

2415
02:50:56,689 --> 02:50:59,071
<i>Moaning could be heard from underground</i>

2416
02:50:59,095 --> 02:51:01,269
<i>But no one was found</i>

2417
02:51:01,293 --> 02:51:05,209
<i>(In 1888 on December the 15th)</i>

2418
02:51:05,233 --> 02:51:07,698
<i>(In the Windknight’s Lot Paper)</i>

2419
02:51:07,698 --> 02:51:09,627
<i>An eye-witness reported</i>

2420
02:51:09,628 --> 02:51:11,721
<i>That the following day, below a cliff</i>

2421
02:51:11,721 --> 02:51:13,594
<i>Men were seen burning clothing</i>

2422
02:51:13,594 --> 02:51:16,412
<i>(And destroying something with a hammer)</i>

2423
02:51:16,413 --> 02:51:18,030
<i>It seemed to be a stone mask</i>

2424
02:51:18,054 --> 02:51:22,171
<i>(In 1889 on February the 2nd)</i>

2425
02:51:22,171 --> 02:51:25,792
<i>(In the announcements section)</i>

2426
02:51:25,887 --> 02:51:30,393
<i>(The Joestar heir)</i>

2427
02:51:30,418 --> 02:51:34,432
<i>(Jonathan Joestar, of Liverpool, was wed)</i>

2428
02:51:34,456 --> 02:51:39,994
<i>(To the Pendletons’
daughter, Erina Pendleton)</i>

2429
02:51:40,382 --> 02:51:42,058
<i>In a small notice, they announced:</i>

2430
02:51:42,058 --> 02:51:46,600
<i>The honeymoon would be a trip
to the United States by steamer</i>

2431
02:51:46,601 --> 02:51:50,030
<i>(Now, on to other news...)</i>

2432
02:51:51,857 --> 02:51:53,762
Mr. Joestar! Both of you!

2433
02:51:53,762 --> 02:51:55,301
Best of wishes!

2434
02:51:55,528 --> 02:51:57,487
I’ll always be there for you!

2435
02:51:57,520 --> 02:52:01,124
If you’re in trouble, I’ll rush anywhere!

2436
02:52:01,171 --> 02:52:03,328
Happy honeymoon!

2437
02:52:03,328 --> 02:52:06,176
I can’t wait to hear all about it!

2438
02:52:06,785 --> 02:52:08,785
America, how nice!

2439
02:52:09,110 --> 02:52:11,324
I wanna go there too,

2440
02:52:11,325 --> 02:52:13,922
And try to dig up some oil for myself!

2441
02:52:14,354 --> 02:52:15,878
Damn it...

2442
02:52:17,026 --> 02:52:20,709
But after this, a fateful
moment was soon to come...

2443
02:52:21,169 --> 02:52:25,359
This story will be passed down
until the world has come full circle.

2444
02:52:25,360 --> 02:52:30,154
That will be the life’s work
of Speedwagon the meddler...

2445
02:52:30,463 --> 02:52:34,991
But, the one to tell you what
happens right now won’t be me...

2446
02:52:43,327 --> 02:52:48,137
<i>I pray that today will never end</i>

2447
02:52:48,137 --> 02:52:51,240
<i>In the midst of a carousel of stars</i>

2448
02:52:51,741 --> 02:53:00,116
<i>Let my hand always be in yours</i>

2449
02:53:00,414 --> 02:53:01,716
What’s wrong?

2450
02:53:04,970 --> 02:53:06,923
When you’re next to me...

2451
02:53:07,702 --> 02:53:09,119
I’m happy!

2452
02:53:09,508 --> 02:53:11,143
I feel the same.

2453
02:53:11,508 --> 02:53:13,603
I wish you could’ve met my father...

2454
02:53:14,389 --> 02:53:16,198
Well, let’s go and eat!

2455
02:53:21,101 --> 02:53:22,101
Jonathan?

2456
02:53:22,927 --> 02:53:23,927
That’s...

2457
02:53:27,869 --> 02:53:28,869
Erina,

2458
02:53:29,901 --> 02:53:31,338
Go back to our cabin.

2459
02:53:32,036 --> 02:53:33,983
Don’t forget to lock the door!

2460
02:53:44,455 --> 02:53:46,562
I have lured him here.

2461
02:53:47,201 --> 02:53:48,897
My body...

2462
02:53:50,273 --> 02:53:51,767
Have you come?

2463
02:53:53,074 --> 02:53:54,074
Dio...

2464
02:53:54,576 --> 02:53:55,576
JoJo...

2465
02:53:57,431 --> 02:54:01,778
I dare show myself in this pitiful
state in front of you for a reason...

2466
02:54:03,399 --> 02:54:05,783
I used to despise you so much,

2467
02:54:06,022 --> 02:54:08,419
But now I respect you...

2468
02:54:09,000 --> 02:54:10,989
That’s because I’ve realised something!

2469
02:54:13,436 --> 02:54:16,692
If there is a God that controls fate,

2470
02:54:17,546 --> 02:54:21,330
Then there’s never been a relationship
orchestrated as perfectly as ours...

2471
02:54:22,788 --> 02:54:26,369
You’re the reason I got this power,

2472
02:54:27,184 --> 02:54:29,572
And you’re the reason why...

2473
02:54:30,413 --> 02:54:33,542
The world has slipped from my grasp!

2474
02:54:34,474 --> 02:54:35,811
When will it...

2475
02:54:36,879 --> 02:54:37,837
Be enough for you?

2476
02:54:37,837 --> 02:54:40,449
That’s exactly what our destiny is!

2477
02:54:41,837 --> 02:54:47,356
I’ll obtain the body of the one and
only person I respect in this world.

2478
02:54:47,999 --> 02:54:51,327
And live in eternal glory!

2479
02:54:52,678 --> 02:54:54,416
JoJo...

2480
02:54:55,527 --> 02:54:57,535
You and I...

2481
02:54:58,289 --> 02:55:01,305
Are one and the same in this world!

2482
02:55:04,700 --> 02:55:07,383
Lord Dio! Look, look, look!

2483
02:55:07,384 --> 02:55:09,542
Please look!

2484
02:55:10,153 --> 02:55:11,566
Jonathan!

2485
02:55:13,519 --> 02:55:15,850
<i>From light to darkness</i>

2486
02:55:15,858 --> 02:55:17,961
<i>This is the start of my mythos</i>

2487
02:55:17,962 --> 02:55:20,123
<i>I will end it all</i>

2488
02:55:20,124 --> 02:55:22,148
<i>And restart it all</i>

2489
02:55:22,399 --> 02:55:24,820
<i>For this is Dio’s World!</i>

2490
02:55:24,821 --> 02:55:26,376
Right, Erina Joestar?

2491
02:55:26,377 --> 02:55:27,210
Dio!

2492
02:55:27,232 --> 02:55:30,986
<i>I can’t speak—can’t breathe—</i>

2493
02:55:31,478 --> 02:55:33,035
<i>My ripple!</i>

2494
02:55:33,272 --> 02:55:35,296
Erina! Not you too!

2495
02:55:35,948 --> 02:55:39,305
<i>This is the start of his mythos!</i>

2496
02:55:39,313 --> 02:55:44,947
<i>This ark is swarming with his followers!</i>

2497
02:55:46,790 --> 02:55:47,988
Please, spare the child!

2498
02:55:48,726 --> 02:55:49,726
Run!

2499
02:55:49,933 --> 02:55:51,473
Shall we torture him to death?!

2500
02:55:51,474 --> 02:55:54,395
Or maybe enjoy watching him asphyxiate?!

2501
02:55:54,401 --> 02:55:55,489
Wang Chan!

2502
02:55:56,621 --> 02:56:00,803
<i>Painlessly cut his head
from his shoulders!</i>

2503
02:56:00,804 --> 02:56:03,098
<i>I won’t tolerate any insults!</i>

2504
02:56:03,099 --> 02:56:05,358
<i>My friend, Jonathan Joestar—</i>

2505
02:56:05,778 --> 02:56:08,990
<i>I’ll take you as my own</i>

2506
02:56:08,990 --> 02:56:14,486
<i>Your blood will become my future!</i>

2507
02:56:14,549 --> 02:56:17,947
<i>I’ll tie our futures together</i>

2508
02:56:18,602 --> 02:56:22,832
<i>With my final ripple!</i>

2509
02:56:22,888 --> 02:56:26,722
<i>JoJo!</i>

2510
02:56:26,977 --> 02:56:31,750
<i>JoJo!</i>

2511
02:56:42,052 --> 02:56:48,051
<i>I felt it tear. Something
important inside me just tore</i>

2512
02:56:48,135 --> 02:56:49,135
Jonathan!

2513
02:56:51,257 --> 02:56:53,247
ERINA: How could this be?!
JOJO: Get out of here!

2514
02:56:53,952 --> 02:56:55,951
I won’t, JoJo...

2515
02:56:56,658 --> 02:57:04,960
<i>I will burn with you</i>

2516
02:57:04,960 --> 02:57:13,135
<i>Until everything turns to ash</i>

2517
02:57:17,595 --> 02:57:19,857
<i>(The flash of flames)</i>

2518
02:57:19,905 --> 02:57:21,835
<i>Everything is connected</i>

2519
02:57:21,841 --> 02:57:23,912
<i>You can’t ask me to live!</i>

2520
02:57:23,913 --> 02:57:25,969
<i>There’s a meaning to it all!</i>

2521
02:57:25,976 --> 02:57:28,545
<i>JOJO: It’s alright if you cry
ERINA: Your courage is too cruel!</i>

2522
02:57:28,545 --> 02:57:30,376
<i>JOJO: You will be
ERINA: I will be</i>

2523
02:57:30,377 --> 02:57:34,046
<i>The one to spin the thread of fate</i>

2524
02:57:34,081 --> 02:57:38,017
{\an8}<i>(Flames are burning everything up)</i>

2525
02:57:34,401 --> 02:57:41,096
<i>Just like my mother
died for me, I’ll—</i>

2526
02:57:38,104 --> 02:57:42,318
{\an8}<i>(Light and darkness flicker and flash)</i>

2527
02:57:42,342 --> 02:57:46,001
{\an8}<i>(Flames are burning everything up)</i>

2528
02:57:42,684 --> 02:57:44,570
<i>Farewell!</i>

2529
02:57:44,570 --> 02:57:46,297
<i>I’m still alive! </i>

2530
02:57:46,530 --> 02:57:52,207
<i>In the end, I, Dio, will triumph!</i>

2531
02:57:46,555 --> 02:57:50,253
{\an8}<i>(Light and darkness flicker and flash)</i>

2532
02:57:52,439 --> 02:57:57,257
<i>My mythos begins here</i>

2533
02:57:57,257 --> 02:58:00,209
<i>JoJo!</i>

2534
02:58:06,732 --> 02:58:08,691
I know what you’re like...

2535
02:58:10,493 --> 02:58:11,824
I figured...

2536
02:58:12,777 --> 02:58:14,253
You would strike...

2537
02:58:15,475 --> 02:58:16,917
Before I...

2538
02:58:20,132 --> 02:58:21,532
Lost consciousness.

2539
02:58:24,060 --> 02:58:25,060
JoJo?

2540
02:58:25,980 --> 02:58:27,488
Let me go, JoJo!

2541
02:58:31,337 --> 02:58:32,337
He’s...

2542
02:58:36,696 --> 02:58:37,696
Dead...

2543
02:58:59,799 --> 02:59:04,480
<i>[AZTEC CHANTING]</i>

2544
02:59:14,181 --> 02:59:19,628
<i>That proud life of his</i>

2545
02:59:20,213 --> 02:59:24,266
<i>Vanished into the dusts of time</i>

2546
02:59:24,881 --> 02:59:29,101
<i>But this fateful adventure</i>

2547
02:59:29,744 --> 02:59:34,309
<i>Will become an inheritance</i>

2548
02:59:34,356 --> 02:59:37,165
<i>Passed down forever</i>

2549
02:59:39,502 --> 02:59:41,756
<i>His golden spirit</i>

2550
02:59:41,778 --> 02:59:45,954
<i>(Phantom Blood)</i>

2551
02:59:51,678 --> 02:59:54,363
<i>Like two who make one,</i>

2552
02:59:54,883 --> 02:59:58,740
<i>We feel a bizarre friendship</i>

2553
02:59:59,899 --> 03:00:02,838
<i>Isn’t that right, Dio?</i>

2554
03:00:03,739 --> 03:00:06,731
<i>If it weren’t for you...</i>

2555
03:00:06,731 --> 03:00:09,310
<i>No, it’s because of you</i>

2556
03:00:09,311 --> 03:00:11,580
<i>Hey, JoJo</i>

2557
03:00:12,153 --> 03:00:14,850
<i>Now I’ll...</i>

2558
03:00:15,706 --> 03:00:19,988
<i>Keep looking at the stars</i>

2559
03:00:20,119 --> 03:00:26,661
<i>Guided by this hapless fate</i>

2560
03:00:27,412 --> 03:00:31,700
<i>We’ll reach out to the stars</i>

2561
03:00:31,833 --> 03:00:38,107
<i>Our two fates</i>

2562
03:00:38,413 --> 03:00:41,903
<i>Have become one</i>

2563
03:00:39,530 --> 03:00:44,443
{\an8}<i>(That immortal poem echoes quietly)</i>

2564
03:00:44,474 --> 03:00:47,371
<i>Until the world</i>

2565
03:00:45,133 --> 03:00:49,084
{\an8}<i>(One saw stars)</i>

2566
03:00:49,679 --> 03:00:53,377
<i>Is born anew</i>

2567
03:00:50,576 --> 03:00:53,505
{\an8}<i>(The stars are shimmering)</i>

2568
03:00:53,583 --> 03:00:55,930
{\an8}<i>(Like blood through a vein,
mud is pulsating)</i>

2569
03:00:55,407 --> 03:00:58,727
<i>I’ll live</i>

2570
03:00:56,216 --> 03:01:00,562
{\an8}<i>(One saw mud)</i>

2571
03:00:59,351 --> 03:01:02,064
<i>I’ll disappear</i>

2572
03:01:02,155 --> 03:01:12,849
<i>JOJO: With you!
DIO: I will live!</i>

2573
03:01:03,425 --> 03:01:08,830
{\an8}<i>(The sunlight yellow gleam shines)</i>

2574
03:01:08,830 --> 03:01:12,987
{\an8}<i>(Let the golden wind blow)</i>

2575
03:01:12,986 --> 03:01:18,505
{\an8}<i>(And the shadow of midnight
blue darkness grows)</i>

2576
03:01:15,733 --> 03:01:19,181
<i>(Living in the shadow of history)</i>

2577
03:01:19,336 --> 03:01:22,317
<i>(We’ll stop the flow of time)</i>

2578
03:01:22,622 --> 03:01:25,493
<i>(Even when the world resets)</i>

2579
03:01:25,494 --> 03:01:28,518
<i>(The tale will keep on being told)</i>

2580
03:01:28,660 --> 03:01:34,692
<i>(This bizarre adventure)</i>

2581
03:01:35,539 --> 03:01:44,573
<i>(Our golden spirit will shine)</i>

2582
03:01:50,019 --> 03:01:53,615
Speedwagon coolly withdraws.

2583
03:06:28,875 --> 03:06:32,833
Thank you for coming
to today’s performance.

2584
03:06:36,974 --> 03:06:38,685
This is a public [streamed] performance.

2585
03:06:38,911 --> 03:06:43,726
Since it’s my and Zeppeli’s actor,
Hirose Yusuke’s, final performance,

2586
03:06:43,751 --> 03:06:47,296
We each wanted to say a
few words if you don’t mind.

2587
03:06:50,032 --> 03:06:51,581
Take it away, Mr. Hirose.

2588
03:06:51,606 --> 03:06:55,893
I had the honour of performing the double
cast role of Zeppeli. I am Hirose Yusuke.

2589
03:06:55,933 --> 03:06:57,933
Thank you for today.

2590
03:07:01,064 --> 03:07:03,313
The musical will close tomorrow, though.

2591
03:07:03,587 --> 03:07:06,913
This type of role has been
played by others before,

2592
03:07:07,453 --> 03:07:11,233
Although personally, I
found that to be relieving.

2593
03:07:11,497 --> 03:07:16,084
There have been many
things that led to this day.

2594
03:07:16,084 --> 03:07:22,153
So even now, I have a lot of
thoughts and a lot of emotions, but...

2595
03:07:22,394 --> 03:07:27,589
Aside from that, the fact that we
have come this far is really thanks to...

2596
03:07:28,013 --> 03:07:33,450
Each and every one of the cast members
on this stage, and the wonderful and skilled staff.

2597
03:07:33,608 --> 03:07:36,192
And foremost, the people
who came every day—

2598
03:07:36,217 --> 03:07:39,854
You’re not coming every day?
Well, every day—

2599
03:07:39,879 --> 03:07:43,433
Truly a lot of fans came
and filled the whole theatre.

2600
03:07:43,458 --> 03:07:45,814
I would like to think our performance’s
quality is thanks to your support.

2601
03:07:45,839 --> 03:07:50,552
Truly, you’ve made each member of
this performance happy. Thank you.

2602
03:07:50,577 --> 03:07:53,073
From the bottom of my heart,

2603
03:07:53,098 --> 03:07:54,695
Pow.

2604
03:07:54,719 --> 03:07:56,719
MAMORU: From the bottom of the heart, pow!

2605
03:08:08,767 --> 03:08:12,804
Well, I played the role of Jonathan
Joestar, I’m Matsushita Yuya.

2606
03:08:12,828 --> 03:08:14,828
Thank you for today!

2607
03:08:16,180 --> 03:08:18,609
Did you have fun, everyone?!

2608
03:08:19,756 --> 03:08:22,557
The best, hearing this is the best, yeah.

2609
03:08:22,977 --> 03:08:26,972
Uh, right. Really, tomorrow’s
truly the final performance.

2610
03:08:26,997 --> 03:08:29,015
That curtain call will
be the grand finale, too.

2611
03:08:29,016 --> 03:08:32,066
I think that Shotaro will
do perfectly tomorrow.

2612
03:08:32,067 --> 03:08:34,485
I—are you worried?

2613
03:08:34,507 --> 03:08:35,335
Nah, it’s probably okay.

2614
03:08:35,180 --> 03:08:36,946
-I’m worried, so please do the speech instead!

2615
03:08:35,917 --> 03:08:37,899
-He’s—that’s in the past.

2616
03:08:37,923 --> 03:08:41,368
Yeah, no. Anyway I think he’ll be fine.

2617
03:08:41,393 --> 03:08:45,543
I wanted to voice some
personal thoughts here.

2618
03:08:45,568 --> 03:08:49,436
First off, as Mr. Hirose said before,

2619
03:08:49,461 --> 03:08:52,656
It’s been a long road to
arrive at our final performance.

2620
03:08:52,681 --> 03:08:54,374
And I’m relieved that we made it.

2621
03:08:54,399 --> 03:08:57,973
Truly, I’m truly happy to
be on this stage. Thank you!

2622
03:09:02,638 --> 03:09:07,211
Back in February, right?
Opening night was delayed.

2623
03:09:07,236 --> 03:09:09,310
But when we made it to opening day,

2624
03:09:09,335 --> 03:09:15,774
At that curtain call, really, at that time,
the audience cheered and applauded a lot,

2625
03:09:15,799 --> 03:09:17,300
Which has continued up through today.

2626
03:09:17,325 --> 03:09:22,257
Truthfully, at that time, I was feeling, within
me, that we became something unforgettable.

2627
03:09:22,282 --> 03:09:29,444
Yes, that’s right. Truly,
thank you for everything.

2628
03:09:29,469 --> 03:09:32,671
For having supported us up to this point.

2629
03:09:32,696 --> 03:09:34,838
And to Mamo, who supported
me like a partner in this.

2630
03:09:34,863 --> 03:09:39,394
Isn’t it seriously amazing that
he did this role without a double?

2631
03:09:39,419 --> 03:09:40,953
MAMORU: It’s alright.
YUYA: No, it was wonderful.

2632
03:09:41,165 --> 03:09:44,162
Before you even started,
I almost cried when I saw your face.

2633
03:09:44,187 --> 03:09:46,088
Yeah, me too a bit! I got emotional!

2634
03:09:46,113 --> 03:09:47,573
MAMORU: Yes.
YUYA: Sorry, I had to excuse myself.

2635
03:09:47,598 --> 03:09:48,568
Excuse yourself...

2636
03:09:48,593 --> 03:09:51,330
YUYA: It wasn’t because of you or something like that that I left.
MAMORU: I get it.

2637
03:09:51,355 --> 03:09:55,659
Nah, you were really incredible.
Really spectacularly incredible.

2638
03:09:55,684 --> 03:09:56,759
MAMORU: Not at all.
YUYA: No, no, I’m sorry.

2639
03:09:56,784 --> 03:10:00,874
It might be unusual for a performer to say this,
but I truly respect you. Really, you’re wonderful.

2640
03:10:00,875 --> 03:10:04,218
MAMORU: No, no really.
YUYA: I thought he really rejected his humanity.

2641
03:10:04,273 --> 03:10:05,668
You were just that wonderful.

2642
03:10:05,692 --> 03:10:07,008
[INAUDIBLE]

2643
03:10:07,032 --> 03:10:09,161
MAMORU: Thanks.
YUYA: Yes. So then...

2644
03:10:09,186 --> 03:10:14,519
We’re not on the same stage
tonight as we were then, but—

2645
03:10:14,544 --> 03:10:23,520
From the first day of rehearsals until now, he’s
supported me, helped me improve, and encouraged me.

2646
03:10:23,545 --> 03:10:30,154
Shotaro too. I truly believe that without those
two, I would never have achieved this JoJo.

2647
03:10:30,293 --> 03:10:34,488
So, this has been my first time
acting in a double cast performance.

2648
03:10:34,513 --> 03:10:38,570
Thank you everyone in the cast!

2649
03:10:38,754 --> 03:10:42,632
It was wonderful. Thanks!

2650
03:10:47,447 --> 03:10:52,128
And above all, above all, truly,
thank you for being devoted like this!

2651
03:10:52,160 --> 03:10:53,656
Now to everyone at the theatre,

2652
03:10:53,681 --> 03:10:58,262
And everyone watching the stream,
I don’t know where the cameras are but—

2653
03:10:58,287 --> 03:11:00,811
Thank you from the bottom of my heart!

2654
03:11:03,306 --> 03:11:04,012
Thanks!

2655
03:11:08,401 --> 03:11:11,584
I was already so relieved that
I could raise my voice today.

2656
03:11:11,654 --> 03:11:17,469
Yes, and tomorrow Mr. Hirose and I will
be watching the final performance together!

2657
03:11:17,494 --> 03:11:19,700
Everyone, do your best!

2658
03:11:19,725 --> 03:11:21,725
I’ll be giving it my all along with you!

2659
03:11:23,435 --> 03:11:26,608
Everyone, make sure
to—what are you saying?

2660
03:11:26,633 --> 03:11:29,990
I’m doing it! I was
just getting to it, okay?!

2661
03:11:30,105 --> 03:11:32,512
I’m gonna watch it too!

2662
03:11:34,081 --> 03:11:36,413
Yeah, I’ll watch too.

2663
03:11:36,845 --> 03:11:37,736
Pardon me.

2664
03:11:37,761 --> 03:11:44,570
And so, please support everyone
through tomorrow’s final performance!

2665
03:11:52,838 --> 03:11:56,769
Truly, thank you for today!

2666
03:11:56,793 --> 03:12:00,793
{\an8}[TN: Everyone’s muted for about 2 min]

2667
03:14:19,689 --> 03:14:21,760
[INAUDIBLE]

2668
03:14:21,817 --> 03:14:23,110
MAMORU: It’s already over.

2669
03:14:23,135 --> 03:14:24,391
[INAUDIBLE]

2670
03:14:24,439 --> 03:14:27,319
Thank you! Thank you!

2671
03:14:27,344 --> 03:14:29,853
Definitely, please support
tomorrow’s performance too!

2672
03:14:29,878 --> 03:14:32,063
Shotaro, do your best tomorrow!

2673
03:14:32,087 --> 03:14:33,809
MAMORU: Do your best!

2674
03:14:34,968 --> 03:14:36,474
Thank you!

2675
03:14:37,365 --> 03:14:38,451
MAMORU: Thanks!

